// 37.745 — 🩹 **/menu-preview broken-image purge — null out `the420bar.com` URLs server-side.** Doug 2026-05-20 "80% of out menu is still messed up" — diagnosed (earlier session): catalog has hundreds of products with `image_url` pointing at `the420bar.com/wp-content/...` (vendor host returning HTTP 405 server-wide). `ProductImage` has client-side onError → gradient-placeholder + brand-logo fallback, but the SSR'd HTML still ships the broken `<img src="https://the420bar.com/...">` and browsers race the fetch before React hydrates + flips state — so cards flash the broken-img glyph on first paint. **Fix:** NEW `safeProductImageUrl()` helper in `lib/banned-logo-url.ts` (sister of existing `safeLogoUrl`); strips known-dead hosts. Set = `["the420bar.com"]` — single-entry today, extensible when next vendor host goes dark. Wired into `lib/db.ts` at all 10 product-row mapping sites (`getMenuProducts`, `getProductsByIds`, `getFeaturedProducts`, `getJustInProducts`, `getDohProducts`, `getNearMenu`, `getStashFeed`, etc.) via single-line sed: `imageUrl: safeProductImageUrl(r.image_url ...)`. Empty imageUrl now correctly routes to placeholder branch on first paint — brand logo (60+ shipped at `/public/brand-logos/`) renders for products whose vendor is on the logo allowlist; category icon for the rest. **NO broken-img glyph possible from a known-dead host going forward.** Sister scc v29.125 same-push. Real fix-of-record is vendor-photo backfill (Inv-App migration 0258 in flight) — this is the bridge until ≥80% photo coverage lands. typecheck CLEAN.
