// 37.685 — 🛡️ Post-login link-follow + open-redirect guard extract — sister scc v29.065 same-push. Ports the brapp v411.545 `lib/safe-redirect.ts` pattern verbatim from `apps/staff/src/lib/safe-redirect.ts` to glw + scc public sites. **Wedge:** a logged-out customer who clicked a deep link to `/account/orders` (e.g. emailed receipt, push-notification land-back, shared link from a friend) would hit `redirect("/sign-in")` and after authenticating land on the default `/account` — not back on the order-history page they actually came for. Now both protected pages pass their own path as `?redirect_url=/account/orders` (and `?redirect_url=/account` from the bare /account hit which can happen via deep-link too) so Clerk lands the customer back where they started. **Companion security wedge:** the inline `safeRedirectPath` previously duplicated at top of sign-in + sign-up pages is lifted to NEW `lib/safe-redirect.ts` (same shape as brapp's). Defends against `?redirect_url=https://attacker.com/phish` open-redirect — Clerk would otherwise honor the attacker-controlled value via `fallbackRedirectUrl`. **Switched from `fallbackRedirectUrl` to `forceRedirectUrl`** on both `<SignIn>` + `<SignUp>` so Clerk uses our validated path deterministically rather than honoring an attacker-controlled value from its own internal redirect state. **Files:** NEW `lib/safe-redirect.ts` (39 LOC) · MOD `app/sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/page.tsx` (-21 +9 LOC — drop inline guard + import shared + force prop) · MOD `app/sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/page.tsx` (-13 +7 LOC same shape) · MOD `app/account/page.tsx` (1 line) · MOD `app/account/orders/page.tsx` (1 line). Other 2 `/sign-in?redirect_url=…` callsites (`/account/profile`, `/account/heroes`, `/order/confirmation/[id]`) already had the destination param so no change needed. typecheck CLEAN. Sister-port of brapp v411.545 + cannagent + VRG same-day. Doctrine pin: `feedback_open_redirect_safe_redirect_path`.

// 37.645 — 🎨 /menu-preview cycle-4 polish — sister-port of scc v29.005 + v29.025 BUNDLED (Doug 2026-05-19 "menu looks like dookei" → 2 SCC rounds shipped + iterated; this is the GLW catch-up bundled as one push to keep build cadence sane). Four ships in one diff: **(1) Brand-logo fallback in ProductImage** — when product has no `image_url` but `brand` maps to a file at `/public/brand-logos/<slug>.png` (60+ brand logos already shipped — exact same files as SCC), render the brand logo at 96px contained INSTEAD of the generic category icon. `onError` gracefully drops back to category icon for brands without a logo file — no per-brand allowlist needed, no broken-image risk. Brand pill suppressed when logo renders. NEW helper `slugifyBrandForLogo` (toLowerCase + non-alphanumeric→hyphen + trim) matches existing public asset convention (`buddy-boy-farm.png`). **(2) DOH chip placement + strain chip move** — DOH chip stacks UNDER the deal chip (`top-12` when deal, `top-2.5` solo) replacing prior collision with deal `%-OFF`. Swapped 🟣 emoji for inline `<svg>` medical cross — reads as clinical regulatory chip (WSLCB extra-tested SKU, no excise tax for verified patients), not consumer marketing. `<TODO swap inline SVG>` comment marks Doug-action site (official WA-DOH logo to drop into chat). Strain chip moved to ALWAYS bottom-right (was conditional top-left when no deal — would have collided with new DOH placement on DOH+strain cards without a deal). Bottom edge now symmetric weight-left / strain-right. **(3) Empty-state next-steps overhaul** — was generic "No products match those filters" + bare "Reset filters" link. Now: bolder primary message · sub-line context ("Some combinations are stricter than what's on the shelf today") · pill-button Clear/Reset CTAs (was tiny underline link) · NEW category-pivot row with top-4 in-stock categories as one-tap buttons that reset all filters + jump to that category. Search-miss path gets distinct copy variant ("Try a shorter search or one of the popular categories below. Still stuck? Call the store and a budtender can check the back.") that includes the phone-the-store fallback. Real users hit empty state when their filter combo over-narrows — the category pivot gets them back to browsing in one tap. **(4) Hero contrast bump** — `text-green-300/70` + `text-green-200/70` on the menu-preview hero were below WCAG AA on the slate-900 background. Now `text-green-100` + `text-green-200/90` — readable, still green-chrome (matches the `text-green-400` eyebrow above). Plus responsive grid-gap `gap-3 sm:gap-4` (was flat `gap-4`). 2 files: `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx` (~125 LOC delta — full v29.005 + v29.025 ports compounded) + `app/menu-preview/page.tsx` (2-line contrast tweak) + version.ts. typecheck CLEAN.

// 37.625 — 🧹 /apply cleanup + Careers nav link (Doug 2026-05-19 reviewing Kat's apply-form screenshot). Two fixes: **(1)** Removed the "WA cannabis worker permit" field — WA does NOT issue a state-level cannabis worker permit (unlike CO's MED badge / NV's agent card / OR's worker permit). Per Doug "No cannabis license needed in washington." Employees must be 21+ per WAC 314-55-115 + complete employer training (responsible vendor, MAST), but no state-issued worker license exists; asking applicants confused them + signaled we expect a permit they can't legally obtain. Removed: 3 sites in `app/apply/page.tsx` — `useState<boolean | null>` declaration, the FormData append branch in handleSubmit, the entire `<Field label="WA cannabis worker permit">` block with its Yes/Not-yet radio set. Server-side API (`/api/applications`) still accepts the field for backwards compat (older cached client bundles in-flight) — it just ignores the absence. DB column `has_wa_worker_permit` stays (prior submissions retain their value). **(2)** Added "Careers" link to `components/SiteHeader.tsx` NAV array (between About + FAQ) — Doug "the apply part isnt anywhere on the website that i can see." `/careers` (job-listings hub page that links to `/apply`) was reachable only via direct-URL or careers footer link before. Now top-of-page on every public route. Sister scc v28.985 same-push (indigo brand instead of green). typecheck CLEAN.

// 37.605 — 🩹 /apply UX hardening — Doug 2026-05-19 reported (third-hand via Tyler) a Wenatchee applicant tried to upload a resume + "wouldn't let them" — no specific error captured. Top failure-mode candidates: (a) ~70% PDF-only gate (.doc/.docx/.pages/phone-photo rejected client-side), (b) ~20% disabled-Submit confusion (some other required field empty, button greyed silently with no signal which field was blocking), (c) ~5% file >10MB, (d) <5% backend (health/api/applications green; no source=applications.* rows in /admin/errors unresolved sample). Two defensive UX adds covering (a)+(b)+(c). Sister scc v28.965 same-push. **(A) PDF-rejection copy + always-visible "How to make a PDF" disclosure.** Type rejection: "Resume must be a PDF." → "This file isn't a PDF. We only accept PDFs — see the conversion tips just below." Size rejection includes the actual file size + actionable nudge: "Your file is X.X MB — the limit is 10 MB. Try saving with smaller images, or scan at a lower resolution." Below the drop zone, NEW collapsed `<details>` with summary "Not sure how to make a PDF?" (green-700 text on glw / indigo-700 on scc) — opens to Word (File → Save As → PDF), Apple Pages (File → Export To → PDF), Google Docs (File → Download → PDF Document), and the iPhone Notes "Scan Documents" → Save to Files as PDF recipe for paper resumes. **`<details>` placed OUTSIDE the `<label>` wrapper** so the summary doesn't trigger the file picker via implicit label-input association — clicking the summary just toggles the disclosure as intended. **(B) "Still needed: …" hint under disabled Submit button.** Pre-fix the button greyed silently when any of {name, valid email, phone, PDF resume, first reference name+phone, 21+ checkbox} was empty — applicants had no signal which field was blocking. Refactored: `missing: string[]` enumerated client-side via 7 length/regex checks; `canSubmit = !submitting && missing.length === 0`; new `<p className="text-center text-xs text-stone-500 -mt-2">Still needed: {missing.join(", ")}.</p>` renders directly under the button only when `!canSubmit && missing.length > 0 && !submitting`. Field labels human-readable: "your name" / "a valid email" / "a phone number" / "a PDF resume" / "first reference's name" / "first reference's phone" / "the 21+ confirmation". WAC/compliance scope unchanged (no field changes; no photo-collection, no DOB, no SSN — RCW 49.60 / EEOC pre-offer guidance preserved). Server-side API contract at `apps/staff/src/app/api/applications/route.ts` untouched. 2 files per stack: `app/apply/page.tsx` (~50 LOC delta) · `lib/version.ts`. typecheck CLEAN.

// 37.585 — 📱 viewport-arc completion — Expert Review #2 caught 2 missed sticky-top surfaces during the 2026-05-18 cross-stack PWA viewport-fit arc closure (glw v37.545 originally claimed "fully complete"). Sister scc v28.945 same-push. **Missed surfaces:** `app/deals/page.tsx:372` (category-filter chip strip `sticky top-0 z-20`) + `app/learn/LearnProgress.tsx:68` (signed-in progress chip strip `sticky top-0 z-20`). Both are scroll-anchored at viewport-top and would clip under iPhone Dynamic Island in PWA mode once the SiteHeader scrolls past — same defect class as the headers shipped in v37.545 + AnnouncementBar/SiteHeader. **Fix:** added `pt-[env(safe-area-inset-top)]` to the deals filter (no existing py to preserve, bare env is correct) + `pt-[max(0.75rem,env(safe-area-inset-top))]` to LearnProgress (preserves the existing `py-3` 12px minimum on non-safe-area devices per the doctrine memory pin `feedback_viewportfit_cover_safe_area_doctrine_2026_05_18`). 2 files. Doctrine pin updated to note the per-page sticky audit gap caught by Expert #2 — recipe should include `grep -rn "sticky top-\|fixed top-0" app/ src/` not just `components/`. typecheck CLEAN. **Caught by Expert 2 in 2-expert cascade review per Doug's "have a expert review the work, have another expert review it afterward" directive.**

