// 37.545 — 📱 viewportFit:"cover" added to root `app/layout.tsx` viewport export — extends the rendered surface UNDER iPhone Dynamic Island / notch / home-indicator safe areas instead of letting mobile Safari pad the whole document. Sister scc v28.905 same-push. Surfaced 2026-05-18 by mobile-PWA expert audit (`/CODE/Green Life/AGENT_BOARD.md` NEXT-UP item (k)). Without this, customers running the site as a PWA (Add-to-Home-Screen) see a black letterbox bar at the top of the screen on notched iPhones — the document body refuses to extend under the Dynamic Island until viewportFit declares it's safe. **Regression-defense bundled in same ship:** pre-commit Explore review flagged that with the document now extending under the notch, the top-edge UI elements (AnnouncementBar at the body's first child + the sticky SiteHeader at `top-0`) would have their content clipped under the Dynamic Island in PWA mode. Fixed in same push: AnnouncementBar root gains `pt-[max(0.25rem,env(safe-area-inset-top))]` (preserves the prior `py-1` minimum on non-safe-area devices) and SiteHeader root gains `pt-[env(safe-area-inset-top)]` (so the header bg extends UP into the notch area while the inner `h-16` nav row stays positioned cleanly below). Pre-existing safe-area padding on sticky bottom CTAs (MobileStickyCta, OrderMenu bottom rail, InstallAppBanner) is what this viewport change finally activates. WAC unchanged (no copy). 5 files per stack: `app/layout.tsx` (viewport export) + `components/AnnouncementBar.tsx` (top safe-area) + `components/SiteHeader.tsx` (top safe-area) + `lib/version.ts` × 2. typecheck CLEAN — `as const` keeps the union-literal narrow for Next.js's Viewport type.

// 37.525 — 🖼️ CLS hardening on /treasure-chest product cards — added explicit width={400} height={400} attrs to the raw `<img>` at app/treasure-chest/page.tsx:54. Sister scc v28.865 same-push. Surfaced by org-wide Vercel perf audit 2026-05-18 (`/CODE/VERCEL_PERF_AUDIT_2026_05_18.md` MEDIUM LOW #1). Parent has `aspect-square` wrapper so visible CLS impact is already small — this is belt-and-suspenders: helps older browsers that don't compute intrinsic ratio from CSS reliably, helps the slow-network LCP measurement before CSS settles, and counts toward Core Web Vitals image-aspect-ratio scoring. Real photo path only (placeholder branch is a div, not an img). 1-file delta. typecheck CLEAN.

// 37.505 — 🎨 /menu-preview placeholder — cycle 3 of 3 (FINAL polish post cycle-2 expert review). Sister scc v28.845 same-push. Three cycle-3 picks shipped: **(1)** LINE-ART SVG ICONS replace emoji — cycle-2 expert review flagged emoji as "the single largest feels-amateur tell" remaining on the card (OS-dependent rendering: Apple color glyph vs Segoe vs Noto Android, jar-emoji 🫙 reads as generic container not pre-roll). NEW file `lib/product-placeholder-icons.tsx` (208 LOC) — 12 inline Lucide-style SVG components (Flower cannabis-leaf · PreRoll joint-cylinder · Vape pen + mouthpiece · Concentrate diamond · Edible gummy + sugar specks · Beverage bottle · Capsule pill · Tincture dropper · Topical squeeze-tube · Accessory bag · Default circle-fallback) all viewBox 0 0 24 24, stroke=currentColor strokeWidth=1.5 strokeLinecap=round strokeLinejoin=round. Exports `getCategoryIcon(category)` returning a `ComponentType<SVGProps<SVGSVGElement>>`. Consumer in `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx` ProductImage no-photo branch: replaces `<span text-6xl>{emoji}</span>` with `<CategoryIcon className="w-14 h-14 text-stone-700/70 drop-shadow-sm" aria-hidden />` — currentColor inheritance puts the icon UNDER the brand pill in the visual hierarchy instead of competing. 56px sized close to the cycle-2 6xl emoji visual weight but with cross-OS-consistent stroke quality. CAT_ICONS emoji map KEPT (4 other use-sites: category-filter chips, navigation glyphs — those stay emoji because `text-base` filter-chip is a different visual register). **(2)** GRADIENT SATURATION POLISH — `lib/product-placeholder.ts` dropped `via-slate-50` middle stop in Capsule entries on both stacks (had killed the saturation cycle-2 was trying to deliver). glw Capsule now `from-emerald-50 via-green-50 to-lime-50`; scc Capsule now `from-indigo-50 via-violet-50 to-blue-50`. Accessory was already correct on cycle 2, no change there. **(3)** THC% PILL FRAME — cycle-2 ship had THC% as free-floating text (`text-[10px] font-semibold`)