// 37.105 — 🎨 Family Album UX polish pass — `/strains/families` + `/strains/families/[family]` × 10 (sister scc v28.465 same-push). Senior-UX tightening pass on the 30-min-old Family Album surface. **Per-family page (`app/strains/families/[family]/page.tsx`) — 5 changes:** (1) **Hero air trim** — pt-6 pb-10 → pt-4 pb-6 (saves ~40px above-the-fold on mobile); margins between eyebrow → h1 → tagline → chip-row collapsed by ~30%. (2) **Dropped "Founder: X" hero chip** — the founder section is the very next block below, so the chip was duplicating the same data 100px later. Cleared the chip-row to just "{N} strains in the line" which actually adds info the prose doesn't. (3) **Preview banner demotion** — was a full bordered amber box (`rounded-md border border-amber-300 bg-amber-50`) consuming a full row; now an inline muted suffix on the eyebrow row (`· preview (not yet indexed)`). Same info, ~60px shorter, less attention-grabbing for the noindex-staging case which is the typical state. (4) **Founder eyebrow muted** — `text-emerald-700` → `text-stone-500` so the eyebrow stops competing with the "Open X page →" CTA-link emerald color inside the founder card directly below. Also dropped the redundant `<h2>The line starts with {anchor.name}</h2>` — the founder card name renders the same string one line lower; removing the h2 saves a row + lets the card carry the visual weight unopposed. Eyebrow text changed from "Founder" → "Founder strain" (slightly more self-explanatory). (5) **Tile-grid header collapse + disclosure for dense families** — pre-fix had eyebrow "The line" + h2 "Strains in The Kush Line" — three uses of "Line" inside ~6 words. Collapsed to single h2 "All {N} strain(s) on the shelf" — countdown frames the surface, no Line-on-Line redundancy. For families >12 strains (kush 32, blueberry 8 → unaffected, but kush + cookies + diesel triggered) the tail hides behind a server-rendered `<details>` disclosure with summary "Show all {N} strains ▾". Zero JS — `<details