// 37.065 — 🌿 Strain Family Album SHIPPED — `/strains/families/[family]` per-genetic-lineage hub × 10 families (sister scc v28.405 same-push). Spec at `/CODE/Green Life/STRAIN_LIBRARY_FAMILY_ALBUM_SPEC_2026_05_16.md`. **What ships:** 9 founder families (Kush · Cookies · Haze · Diesel · Cheese · Skunk · Blueberry · Afghani · Northern Lights) + 1 landrace bucket (Durban Poison, Acapulco Gold, Thai, Colombian, Hawaiian, Panama Red) all at `/strains/families/<slug>`. **Files NEW (per stack):** `lib/strain-families.ts` (333 LOC SSoT — STRAIN_FAMILIES const + getFamily + getFamilyForStrain + getStrainsInFamily + getFounderAnchors + parentWalkReaches BFS) · `components/FamilyMiniTree.tsx` (228 LOC dialed-down SVG fork of StrainLineageTree — thumb 320×140 + spotlight 480×220 size variants, DO NOT mutate original) · `components/FamilyAlbumGrid.tsx` (96 LOC reusable type-color-coded tile grid, compact + standalone modes) · `app/strains/families/page.tsx` (192 LOC hub page, CollectionPage + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD) · `app/strains/families/[family]/page.tsx` (340 LOC per-family hub: hero + founder spotlight + mini-tree + member tile grid + auto-FAQ + cross-link strip + JSON-LD × 3) · `app/strains/families/[family]/opengraph-image.tsx` (208 LOC type-color sister-of-strain OG cards, generateImageMetadata pre-bakes 10 cards at build). **Files MOD:** `app/sitemap.ts` (+24 LOC SEO_FAMILY_WAVE env-gate for 11 new URLs, IIFE pattern at sister tier to SEO_STRAIN_WAVE) · `app/strains/page.tsx` (+45 LOC in-hero "Lens:" anchor-link switcher + new "Browse by genetic line" Family Album section between Type cards and A-Z grid, zero JS, scroll-mt-16 anchor targets). **Routing model: Option A** — `/strains/families/<family>` new sub-path avoids the Next.js 16 ambiguous-route trap that cost 6 stalled deploys via `_type-handler.tsx` fix. `_type-handler.tsx` UNTOUCHED. Per-strain canonical URLs UNTOUCHED. Strain type UNTOUCHED. StrainLineageTree.tsx UNTOUCHED. **WAC 314-55-155 STRICT clean:** family descriptions describe lineage + breeding heritage + supply-chain framing only — zero efficacy/medical/promissory claims. Borderline-watched: Diesel "energetic flower density" + Cheese "customers who specifically chase the funk" + Northern Lights "forgiving" — all framed as breeder-selection or customer-behavior observations, not promised effects. **Cadence-gate compliant:** 11 new URLs (1 hub + 10 family pages) gated by NEW `SEO_FAMILY_WAVE` env (default 0 = all noindex + omitted from sitemap). When Doug bumps to 6 → hub + 5 families enter sitemap; bump to 11 → full surface live. Page-level robots also gated by SEO_STRAIN_WAVE>=1 so dormant build doesn't index even via direct-URL share. **Family membership algorithm:** triple-fallback — (a) explicit includeSlugs list (e.g. Kush includes `og-kush` + `hindu-kush` + `bubba-kush` + `master-kush`), (b) parent-walk BFS up to depth 6 to reach the anchor or any includeSlug (e.g. Blue Dream → Blueberry parent → Blueberry family), (c) nameMatches substring fallback (e.g. any "Kush" in the name catches Bubba Kush, Master Kush, OG Kush). Pure functions, build-time computable, no caching needed at 250-strain dataset scale. **OG cards type-color coded** sister of strain OG generator (Kush hybrid → emerald, Northern Lights indica → indigo, Diesel sativa → orange, Landrace → neutral stone). generateImageMetadata pre-bakes all 10 cards at build for CDN cache. typecheck CLEAN both stacks. efficacy-claims gate CLEAN.
// 37.045 — 🎨 Type-page strain card air + density (polish-audit move #4). Sister scc v28.345 same-push. Pre-this-ship `/strains/{indica,sativa,hybrid}` rendered 70-111 strain cards (after the v36.885 wave-gate-lift) at `lg:grid-cols-3` with cramped `px-4 py-3` padding + no scan-signals beyond name + lineage. Audit verdict: "cognitive overload — eye doesn't know which strain to land on. Each card looks identical." Three changes per audit: (1) **Conditional grid density** — drop `lg:grid-cols-3` → `lg:grid-cols-2` when `strainsForType.length > 40`. Type pages with >40 strains (indica, sativa, hybrid) get the wider 2-col layout for readability; CBD page (~10 strains) stays at 3-col. (2) **Card padding bump** — `px-4 py-3` → `px-4 py-4 sm:px-5 sm:py-4` for breathing room (~30% taller per card on lg). (3) **Top-terpene chip** — added a tiny uppercase chip under the lineage line surfacing the dominant terpene name (`text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide` in brand-accent `bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700` on glw / `bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-700` on scc). Customer can scan a column of cards and pattern-match by terpene at a glance — Myrcene-heavy cards vs Limonene-heavy cards become visually distinguishable without clicking. **Single-file diff** in `app/strains/_type-handler.tsx` (+12 LOC per stack). Cross-stack identical structure, brand-accent swap. typecheck CLEAN. Risk per audit: "page gets ~30% taller on lg viewport. That's the intended cost — readability over density." Verified post-deploy at /strains/hybrid (111 cards) + /strains/indica (78 cards) — both type pages now render at the wider 2-col layout with breathing room + terpene chip per card. CBD page (`/strains/cbd`, ~10 cards) confirmed staying at 3-col since the threshold is 40. **Compounds with prior polish ships:** v36.925 typography unification + v36.945 width-jitter + v36.965 H2 hierarchy + v37.025 menu-skeleton all visible on the same `/strains/<type>` browse → /strains/<slug> detail journey.
// 37.025 — 🎨 Polish micro-batch — /menu skeleton loader + dewey slug-alias bio. Sister scc v28.325 same-push. Two unrelated low-risk wins bundled into one ship. **#1 Menu skeleton (polish-audit move #8):** pre-this-ship the `/menu` page rendered an empty `<div id="app">` between server paint and Boost script execution (1-3s warm cache, 8-15s cold). On slow connections customers saw a blank area for 1-6s with no signal anything was loading. MenuFallback's 6s watchdog fires too late for the perceptual window. Fix: server-rendered 12-card skeleton grid (aspect-square placeholders + 3 text-line bars per card, `animate-pulse`) INSIDE `<div id="app">`. Boost overwrites `#app.innerHTML` on hydrate so the skeleton gets cleanly replaced. `aria-hidden="true"` so screen readers skip the loading state. Matches `grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4` of the real product grid for layout continuity. **#2 Dewey slug-alias fix:** `/brands/dewey-cannabis-co-` (trailing-dash slug exists in sitemap and renders 200 but had NO bio because `lib/brand-copy.ts` was keyed `dewey-cannabis-co` without the dash). Fix: duplicate the entire bio entry under the dash-suffixed key. Both URLs now render the same bio + logo. Page-completion-agent flagged this 2026-05-17. **Files:** `app/menu/JaneMenu.tsx` (+24 LOC skeleton inside #app) + `lib/brand-copy.ts` (+12 LOC dewey-cannabis-co- alias entry) per stack. typecheck CLEAN both stacks. **Risk per audit:** "If Boost ever changes mount strategy from `innerHTML =` to `appendChild`, skeleton stays visible alongside product grid." Verified Boost still uses `innerHTML =` (no Boost API change since v26.805 last reviewed). Will surface in next-day check if regresses. Bundle of two cheap wins — each ~5-15 min, no conversion-watch needed, no Doug-decision dependency.
// 37.005 — 🛒 Strain↔menu integration — "In stock today" live-product section on every /strains/<slug> page (Doug greenlit Path B 2026-05-17). Sister scc v28.305 same-push. The strain page used to be "read about Blue Dream + Browse our menu CTA" — customer then had to manually search /menu for matching products. Now: server-side reads the local Postgres products SoT, scores candidates against the strain via name/lineage/terpene matching, and renders up to 6 matched product cards inline between FAQ + Related-strains sections. Each card shows photo + brand + name + THC% + category + price (online-discounted via lib/online-pricing) + match-reason badge (✓ Exact / ~ Parent: X / ~ Crosses to Y / ~ Same terps: A,B). Footer CTA: "See all {strain.name} on the menu →" routes to /menu?q={name}&_attrSource=strains. **Spec:** STRAIN_MENU_INTEGRATION_SPEC_2026_05_17.md (3,500 words). Doug picked Path B (local Postgres) over Path A (Algolia direct) based on agent investigation: (a) the local products table already has every field via the existing MenuProduct shape, (b) iHJ Algolia is currently CORS-rejected on new Vercel origins + active partner-relationship negotiation pending, (c) Algolia couldn't enforce the 365d-rolling brands_with_recent_sales ghost-inventory filter so Path A would still need the local DB query underneath. **Architecture (4 files per stack):** NEW `lib/strain-match.ts` (244 LOC pure scoring — scoreProduct + rankStrainMatches + nameContains word-boundary matcher + nameStem dedup + renderReason label) · NEW `components/StrainInStockSection.tsx` (124 LOC server component — emerald accent on glw, indigo on scc) · MOD `lib/db.ts` (+114 LOC — `getStrainMatchedProducts(strain, opts)` SQL with same DB invariants as `getMenuProducts`: carry_status='active' + latest_inv qty>0 + brands_with_recent_sales 365d window + image_url IS NOT NULL + ILIKE pre-filter on name/lineage stems OR terpene match within same strain.type, LIMIT 80 candidates → JS scoring → top 6) · MOD `app/strains/[slug]/page.tsx` (+28 LOC — flipped `force-static` to `revalidate=300` ISR, added Promise.all fetch of matched products + active deals, rendered StrainInStockSection between FAQ + Related-strains). **Scoring rubric:** +10 exact-name (word-boundary regex), +6 alias, +5 lineage-parent, +5 lineage-child, +3 sibling, +2 per shared terpene cap 3 (only when type matches), +1 type-only fallback. DROP candidates with score<3 (pure-noise) or null image. Dedupe by (brand, name-stem) — same alt-text-scrub regex strips weight/format prefixes like "1g - ". Rank: reason-rank (exact > lineage > terpene > type) → score desc → isNew first → cheaper first. **Doug §7 decisions (all defaults accepted):** card cap 6 · header "In stock today" · HIDE section when 0 matches · SKIP CBD strains entirely (products.strain_type enum doesn't have a cbd value) · keep weight variants (post-dedupe). **Cache:** Page-level ISR 5min + React.cache() per render wraps getStrainMatchedProducts so re-renders within a request reuse the result. No edge cache headers beyond Next.js defaults. No on-demand revalidation. **Zero new env vars · zero schema changes · zero API routes · zero new third-party dependencies.** Uses existing DATABASE_URL + STRAINS dataset + buildLineageGraph + online-pricing engine + ActiveDeal type + getProductPlaceholderGradient + withAttr. **WAC 314-55-155 clean:** match-reason badges are factual ("Parent: X" / "Same indica"), no efficacy claims. THC% display is OK per WSLCB convention. /menu CTA primacy preserved — the "See all X on the menu" footer link IS the conversion path, not a competitor to /menu. **Build envelope:** ~6 hours estimated, actual ~3 hours via spec-driven build. typecheck CLEAN both stacks. efficacy-claims gate CLEAN. Real product feature, not just polish.
