// 36.945 — 🎨 Polish batch — strain-detail width jitter + iHJ menu alt-text scrub. Sister scc v28.245 same-push. Two polish-audit moves bundled. **Discovered + skipped:** Audit move #2 (focus-visible rings WCAG 2.4.7) was already satisfied via existing `:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #16a34a }` rule in `app/globals.css` from Doug's 2026-05-07 ADA pass — the audit's grep was for Tailwind utility-class strings which underestimate the actual CSS coverage. No new work needed. **Move #3 — strain-detail width jitter fix:** pre-this-ship the `/strains/<slug>` page sections oscillated `max-w-5xl → max-w-2xl → max-w-5xl → max-w-3xl → max-w-3xl → max-w-3xl → max-w-5xl → max-w-3xl` — the eye gets dragged inward 200px, snapped back out for the lineage tree, then inward again. Audit said it "feels like 4 different pages stitched together." Fix: standardized on `max-w-3xl` for prose + cards; kept `max-w-5xl` ONLY on the lineage-tree section (line 259) which legitimately needs the width for its SVG family graph. **Specific changes:** line 213 (breadcrumb rail) + line 218 (hero section) + line 362 (related-strains grid) → `max-w-5xl` → `max-w-3xl`. **Move #6 — iHJ Boost alt-text scrubber:** pre-this-ship `/menu` product image alts shipped with internal SKU codes — `alt="(1 in Returns) Banana OG Cart - 1g - Concentrate - (H)"` — screen-reader hostile + SEO-poor. Audit: "A screen-reader user hears 'open paren one in returns paren Banana OG Cart hyphen one gram...' — incomprehensible. SEO-wise, image search indexes these strings literally." **Fix:** added `MutationObserver`-backed alt-text scrubber as a 4th `<Script id="jane-alt-text-scrub" strategy="afterInteractive">` in `app/menu/JaneMenu.tsx`. The observer strips three patterns: (a) leading `(N in Returns) ` prefix, (b) trailing ` - (H)/(S)/(I)/etc` type marker (1-3 uppercase letter parens), (c) leading `1g - ` / `28g - ` weight+format prefix. Idempotent — re-running on an already-scrubbed alt is a no-op (the regex won't match cleaned strings). Throttled to once per 500ms via `lastRun` timestamp check — light perf impact across menu refresh cycles. **Observer mounts on `document.body`** with `{ childList: true, subtree: true }`; handles both fast-DOMContentLoaded + already-loaded paths. **Sister scc identical change** — both stacks use the same Boost embed + alt patterns. **Effort:** 20min total (5min for #3, 15min for #6). **Risk:** #3 hero card may feel narrower — per audit "that's the point; it'll align with the body copy underneath." #6 MutationObserver runs every menu refresh, throttled to 500ms cap. Verified post-deploy `/menu` still renders products + new alts strip cleanly. typecheck CLEAN both stacks.
