// 36.485 — 🟣 DOH-medical online pricing (Doug 2026-05-17 'build it'). Sister of inv-app v406.525 schema ship. When a SKU is flagged `is_doh_compliant` in the staff app: every product card on `/menu-preview` + `/order` now carries a small purple 🟣 DOH badge top-left of the image (informational for all customers — these are the extra-tested SKUs that pass the WA DOH tier on top of the WSLCB safety panel). When the signed-in customer is ALSO DOH-card-verified (`customers.doh_verified_at` non-null per inv-app migration 0262, staff sets this in /admin/customers/[id] via the new DohVerifyPanel): the card swaps the rec/online-discount price block for a **medical no-tax** price tier — rec price strikethrough above + purple medical-no-tax headline + 🟣 "Medical · no tax" sub-label. Math: shelf prices are tax-inclusive, so medical price = `effective_online_price / (1 + EXCISE_RATE + SALES_TAX_RATE)`. Wenatchee defaults: 37% excise + 8.8% sales = divisor 1.458 → ~31.4% off the post-online-discount price (BOTH tax tiers stripped per RCW 82.08.9998 + RCW 69.50.535(6)(a) since the DOH-card path is the full-exemption tier, NOT the recommending-physician path which only strips sales tax). Env-overridable via `NEXT_PUBLIC_EXCISE_RATE` + `NEXT_PUBLIC_SALES_TAX_RATE` for non-WA tenant deploys. Non-DOH-verified customers + non-DOH-compliant products: zero change to current rendering. **New SSoT:** `lib/medical-pricing.ts` with pure `medicalNoTaxPrice(shelfPrice)` helper. **New customer-state lookup:** `getMedicalStatusByClerkId(clerkUserId)` in `lib/portal.ts` returns `{ isMedical, dohVerifiedAt }` — same Clerk-user → portal_users → customers email-join the existing `getLoyaltyByClerkId` uses. **Two callers wired:** `/menu-preview` + `/order` page-roots resolve dohVerified once (server-side, after Clerk auth resolves) and pass it down through OrderMenu's new `dohVerified?: boolean` prop. **What this does NOT yet do** (Phase 2 of `PLAN_DOH_MEDICAL_TAX_SEPARATION_2026_05_11.md`): the POS register still charges full tax at the till; tax-exempt reconciliation remains off-system at LIQ-1295 filing time. The customer-site display is informational — it tells the patient what they SHOULD ring up at, and signals to staff at pickup that this is a DOH-exempt ticket. typecheck queued.
// 36.465 — 🌿 Smart-suggestion strip on 404 page (Doug 2026-05-16, cross-stack port from inv-app v406.145 / VRG v9.7.192 / GW v2.97.Z60). NEW `app/NotFoundSuggestions.tsx` client component reads `usePathname()` + applies 3 heuristics in priority order: (1) file-suffix paste-error — trailing `/page.tsx`, `/layout.tsx`, `/route.ts`, `/loading.tsx`, etc → strip + suggest clean route. (2) Generic trailing extension (.ts/.tsx/.md/.html/.mdx) → strip. (3) Doubled segment (e.g. `/menu/menu/x` → `/menu/x`) → de-duplicate. When any heuristic fires the 404 page renders a green 'Did you mean?' card between the headline copy and the existing vibe row. Legit 404s render nothing extra — Quick filter + Or try rails stay unchanged. Safety: suggestions anchor to same-origin paths via Next.js `<Link>`; idempotent strip doesn't loop. Wired into `app/not-found.tsx` via 1-line import + single component mount. typecheck clean.
// 36.125 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `check-canonical-or-noindex.mjs` — structural defense against the GSC "Duplicate without user-selected canonical" (2,650 affected items 2026-05-15) + "Duplicate, Google chose different canonical than user" (910 items) buckets that lit up in Doug's GSC screenshot today. **Why these buckets get big:** root `app/layout.tsx` declares `alternates: { canonical: "/" }` as the site-wide default. Per Next 16 metadata cascade, every child page that doesn't override inherits canonical=/. Google reads that as "this is the homepage" and either flags the page as a duplicate (910 bucket — "user claimed canonical=/ but I (Google) disagree") OR fails to read the cascade and flags it as canonical-less (2,650 bucket). Either way the page's content gets dedup'd into homepage in Google's index. **Gate logic:** scans every `app/**/page.tsx` (excluding /api/**, /admin/**, /dev/**, /devmenu/**, /_*/) and requires ONE of: (a) `canonical: "..."` in the page file or its sibling layout.tsx, (b) `robots: { index: false }` or `robots: { noindex: true }` in same locations (the noindex answer for auth/account/admin surfaces), (c) opt-out marker `// canonical:ignore-file` for redirect-only pages that never return content. **Initial scan**: 46 page.tsx files / 1 violation found (`app/brands/page.tsx` — 308-redirects to /menu, never returns content); marker added so the gate skips it. All other 45 already correctly declare own canonical OR noindex (mostly via the v34.105-era audit + sibling layout.tsx workaround for "use client" pages like /alumni). **Note on the 2,650-item GSC bucket itself**: this gate locks the structural class going forward but doesn't directly retroactively fix existing items — many of those URLs are likely (1) iHJ Boost embed query-param deep-links that already canonicalize correctly to /menu (Google will consolidate them on next recrawl), (2) old WordPress URLs that 308-redirect to current canonical equivalents (will fall out of index naturally), (3) `?utm_*` / `?ref=*` tracking-param variants that Google sometimes treats as separate URLs (these consolidate as Google notices the canonical-link parity). Doug-action: in GSC's "Duplicate without user-selected canonical" report, click "Export to Google Sheets" to see the actual URLs — most should be addressable via existing canonicals, but if any cluster shows up that's NOT already handled, we can target it specifically. **Cross-stack scope**: gate idea ports to scc + GW + cannagent + VRG + sureel + inv as those stacks have the same Next 16 metadata cascade. Sister scc port queued. Wired into `.githooks/pre-push` (45/45 gates). Defensive ship — zero behavior change in code paths.
// 36.105 — 🖼️ GSC "Missing field 'image'" structured-data fix across 6 JSON-LD emitters (670 affected items pre-fix, peaked ~1100 on April 30 coinciding with the SEO buildout arc). Doug 2026-05-14 GSC screenshot showed Article/Product validators failing the image-required rule because several emitters either omitted `image` entirely or made it conditional on a nullable column. **6 sites fixed:** (1) `app/brands/[slug]/page.tsx:271` Product schema — was `...(p.image_url ? { image: p.image_url } : {})` (conditional drop, biggest contributor — every product without `image_url` flagged); now `image: p.image_url || brand.logoUrl || ${STORE.website}/brands/${slug}/opengraph-image` — 3-tier fallback always resolves to a valid URL. (2) `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx:251` Article schema — was pointing at root `/opengraph-image` (every post shared one image); now per-route `/blog/${slug}/opengraph-image` so each post gets its own SERP card art via Next 16's per-route OG file convention. (3) `app/learn/[slug]/page.tsx:140` Article schema — was missing `image` field entirely; added `image: [${STORE.website}/learn/${topic.slug}/opengraph-image]`. (4) `app/blog/page.tsx:60` Blog feed BlogPosting items — were missing `image`; added per-post `/blog/${p.slug}/opengraph-image`. (5) `lib/seo-templates.tsx:239` CategoryJsonLd ItemList Product items — were missing `image`; added `image: productImage(p)` using existing helper that handles imageUrl + /api/product-image fallback. (6) `app/press/page.tsx:35` — was typed `NewsArticle` with no image/headline/datePublished/dateModified (validator was flagging all 4 missing); retyped to `WebPage` which is honest (static media-kit page, not date-stamped journalism) and has no required fields we're missing, plus added `primaryImageOfPage` ImageObject pointing at root OG. **Why per-route opengraph-image works as a JSON-LD image fallback**: each affected route already has `app/<route>/opengraph-image.tsx` per Next 16's file convention (v35.505 ship), serving a 1200×630 dynamically-rendered card via ImageResponse — these URLs always resolve, are properly Cache-Control'd at the edge, and Google has been crawling them as the og:image since v35.505. No new files, no new schema dependencies — pure data-shape fix. Sister scc v27.405 same-push (sister stack has same brands/blog/learn/press emitters from prior cross-stack ports). typecheck queued.
