// 23.405 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `check-conflict-markers.mjs` — ported from inv (incident 2026-05-08 01:00 UTC: `CustomerLookup.tsx` had `<<<<<<<` / `=======` / `>>>>>>>` markers committed to inv main since ~v215.805; Vercel rejected every build with "Parsing ecmascript source code failed". 9+ commits stalled in deploy queue for 3+ hours before root cause was diagnosed). Why a separate gate (not just tsc): conflict markers are at the JS-parser level, BEFORE tsc runs. Vercel rejects the file with a parse error so tsc never gets to it. Pre-push tsc runs CLEAN while the actual deploy fails. Guard requires the FULL marker TRIPLE (all of `<<<<<<<`, `=======`, `>>>>>>>`) in same file to avoid false-positives on legitimate `<<<` test fixtures. Scans `.ts/.tsx/.js/.jsx/.mjs/.cjs/.css/.html/.json` across `app/`, `components/`, `lib/`, `scripts/`. 0 offenders today. Wired into pre-push as gate 19 (19/19 OK). Sister scc same-day port.
// 23.305 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `check-usesyncexternalstore-cache.mjs` — pins memory pin `feedback_use_sync_external_store_caching` against future regression. React's `useSyncExternalStore` compares snapshots via `Object.is`. A `getSnapshot` callback returning a fresh array/object reference each call triggers React error #185 (infinite re-render loop) — error bubbles ABOVE the root layout so `app/error.tsx` doesn't catch it; `app/global-error.tsx` takes over showing "This page couldn't load — Reload / Back". Real incident: scc `lib/stash.ts` 2026-05-01 (commit b16ec1b). Guard scans for `useSyncExternalStore` callers (comment-stripped to avoid changelog false-positives) + requires each caller to have a module-level `cached*` variable. Files that only declare the hook without the cache fail. Escape via marker comment `@use-sync-external-store-no-cache` for the rare case where the snapshot is a primitive (Object.is handles it without reference identity). 3/3 callers pass today (CartResumeBanner, recently-viewed, stash). Wired into pre-push as gate 18 (18/18 OK). Sister scc same-day port.
// 23.205 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `check-fabricated-review-schema.mjs` — pins v19.705 (glw) + v13.7405 (scc) AggregateRating + Review JSON-LD strip + memory pin `feedback_fabricated_review_schema_google_policy` against future regression. Emitting Review/AggregateRating schema from hardcoded fake reviews violates Google's "self-serving reviews" policy + FTC scrutiny. Risks a structured-data manual action. Guard scans app/ + components/ + lib/ for `"@type": "Review"` + `"@type": "AggregateRating"` + `"@type": "Rating"`. Opt-out marker `@review-schema-real-reviews-source` lets the future GBP-pull integration (Google approval pending Case 0-8857000041037) emit REAL reviews when it ships. 0 offenders today. Wired into pre-push as gate 17 (17/17 OK). Sister scc same-day port.
// 23.105 — 🚀 Brand-logo image optimization on homepage + /brands/[slug] hero (flagged by vercel:performance-optimizer audit). Pre-fix: `<Image unoptimized>` bypassed Vercel Image Optimization on 10 brand logos sourced from 3rd-party CDNs (Wix, agrocouture, lirp.cdn-website.com, etc.). Total homepage logo weight: **2.7 MB compressed**. Two outliers were egregious: `dose_social_media_graphic-1920w.png` = 1.74 MB rendered at 80×40px, `0b3cc1_ddaf862d...mv2.png` = 710 KB. Same `unoptimized` flag on `/brands/[slug]` hero (rendered at 112×128px). **Fix**: removed `unoptimized` on both call sites + added explicit `sizes` props so the optimizer picks the right responsive variant. Next pipes each through `/_next/image`, resizes to display dimension, serves AVIF/WebP. Expected savings on the two outliers: ~2.5 MB → ~10 KB total. **LCP impact: 1-4s on mobile/3G**, secondary TBT win (less bandwidth contention with JS bundle). Kept `unoptimized` on `DealArt.tsx` (documented iHeartJane CDN edge case) + on per-brand `_brands/*.tsx` pages (lower traffic, optimizer-choke risk per the historical comment). Sister scc same-day port. tsc clean.
