// 21.605 — 🛡️ JSON-LD `</script>` breakout escape wired at 5 missed call sites. `lib/json-ld-safe.ts` `safeJsonLd()` helper has existed since the v2.81-class port, but 5 places were still emitting JSON-LD via raw `JSON.stringify({...})` into `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` — the exact XSS sink the helper exists to prevent. Sites hardened: `app/page.tsx:1250` (HowTo JSON-LD), `app/apply/layout.tsx:55` (BreadcrumbList), `app/learn/page.tsx:151+174` (LearningResource + BreadcrumbList), `app/careers/page.tsx:99` (BreadcrumbList). Each now imports + uses `safeJsonLd()`. Threat model: if any of these JSON-LD payloads ever incorporates admin-edited or DB-sourced strings (blog titles, product copy, vendor names), a value containing `</script>` would break out of the script tag and inject HTML. Today's inputs are developer-hardcoded so real exploitability is near-zero; this is defense-in-depth so a future schema change (e.g. blog post titles in JSON-LD) doesn't silently introduce the vulnerability. Sister of cannagent v5.9085 ldJson() escape + GW already-fixed + scc v13.9505 same-day port. tsc clean.
