// 17.405 — 🖼️ CLS fix on Ray's Lemonade brand-hero image (`/brands/ray-s-lemonade-wa`). Pre-fix the marketing photo `<img>` was `w-full h-auto` with NO parent aspect-ratio class — browser had no way to know intrinsic dimensions before image loaded, so the box rendered 0px tall until paint, then jumped to full-size. Real CLS hit on a customer-facing brand page. Image is 1500×2100 (5:7 portrait, verified via curl + file). Added `width={1500} height={2100}` to the `<img>` — combined with `w-full h-auto` className, browser uses the intrinsic ratio to compute height = (containerWidth × 2100/1500) and reserves space upfront. Continues T34 CLS sweep — that fix shipped 3 of 7 sites (team-avatars on /our-story /community /about); this catches the lone non-aspect-parent variant. The remaining /deals/[id] + /treasure-chest + /brands/[slug] subbrand-logo + scc-equivalents were re-audited and are NOT bugs (parent divs have `aspect-square` or `aspect-[5/2]` reserving space; img inside w-full h-full is fine for CLS). Only the Ray's marketing photo had no aspect-parent. Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 54 CLS sweep re-audit.
