// 16.005 — 🌐 NEW `app/icon.tsx` — favicon-tier 32×32 PNG icon route. Pre-fix glw + scc emitted only `<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="256x256">` + `<link rel="apple-touch-icon">`. Modern browsers prefer PNG > ICO + treat the 32×32 size hint as the canonical small-icon target — without the route, browser tabs fell back to a downscaled 256×256 .ico (decode quality varies by browser/OS, particularly degraded on high-DPI displays + on RSS readers / Slack-preview-card unfurlers that look at `<link rel="icon">` first). Cross-stack symmetric port — GW + cannagent + sureel + vrg all already have an `app/icon.tsx` file emitting Next 16's auto-discovered 32×32 PNG icon route; glw + scc were the lone outliers across the 6-site stack. Brand colors: glw bg=#022c22 fg=#a3e635 (matches manifest theme + body palette). 22-char `G` glyph centered. Verified missing via curl on prod homepage HTML — /icon route absent from glw + scc, present on GW. Sister scc v13.3405 same-port (S glyph on indigo). Caught 2026-05-10 by /loop tick 37 favicon-completeness audit.
