// 15.105 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-og-image-shape.mjs` — pins T29 (og:image shape sweep) + T30 (GW twitter.images alt) against future regression. Walks app/ + lib/, finds every `images: [...]` array inside an `openGraph: {}` or `twitter: {}` block (brace-depth-aware reverse-walk skips arrays in unrelated scopes), fails the build if any element is a literal string or template literal. Bare identifiers (e.g. `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE`) are trusted — agents already reach for the SoT const, and identifier-typed-as-URL is rare. Sister of T22 og-completeness + T27 duplicate-brand-title arc-guards. Verified via injection test (briefly inserted `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` into /about, ran guard, confirmed catch + reverted). Wired into `pnpm check:og-image-shape` (manual). Sister scc v13.2705 + GW v2.95.40 same-push (cross-stack symmetric — same script ports cleanly to all 3 repos).
// 15.005 — 🖼️ og:image shape sweep across 20 page-level openGraph blocks. /loop tick 29 same-class as T19/T20/T21 shallow-overwrite (og:type / og:site_name / og:url) BUT on the `images` field shape. Pre-fix every page set `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` (string form) which emits ONLY `<meta property="og:image">` and OMITS `og:image:width`, `og:image:height`, `og:image:type`, `og:image:alt`. Verified via curl on /about prod: only the bare og:image meta tag emitted, none of the dimension/alt siblings. Without dimensions, share-card crawlers (Facebook, LinkedIn, Slack, Discord, iMessage) can't pre-allocate the share-card image area, falling back to small-card layout or "loading" placeholder until the image fetches. Without alt, accessibility readers + LinkedIn's accessible-mode can't describe the card. The layout already had the proper object-shape (`{ url, width, height, alt }`) but per-page string-form OVERRODE it via shallow-overwrite. Fix: NEW const `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE` exported from `lib/store.ts` with the full shape (`url: "/opengraph-image"`, `width: 1200`, `height: 630`, `alt: "${STORE.name} — Cannabis Dispensary in Wenatchee, WA"`, `type: "image/png"`). Python sweep replaced `images: ["/opengraph-image"]` → `images: [DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE]` across 20 pages: about, apply, blog, blog/[slug], careers, community, deals, deals/[id], faq, find-your-strain, heroes, heroes/[cohort], learn, menu, near, near/[town], order, our-story, treasure-chest, visit. All now emit the full og:image:* meta tag set with proper alt for accessibility. Per-route `opengraph-image.tsx` overrides (e.g. `/menu`, `/brands/[slug]`) still win via Next 16 image-convention precedence — this default only kicks in where there's no per-route override. Sister scc same-push.
// 14.905 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-duplicate-brand-title.mjs` + 4 more catches. Pins the T5/T24/T25 duplicate-brand-title fixes against future regression — when page-level `metadata.title` body bakes in the brand AND the layout's `title.template = '%s | Green Life Cannabis'` appends it, the rendered <title> shows the brand twice. First run caught 4 silent offenders the manual sweeps missed: app/page.tsx homepage (73 chars, brand x2), app/heroes/[cohort]/page.tsx fallback for unknown cohort, app/quiz/unsubscribe/page.tsx (noindex'd but still emits double-brand), app/vendor-access/page.tsx. Implementation: brace-depth-aware regex that SKIPS title declarations inside `openGraph: {}` / `twitter: {}` / other sub-blocks (where brand-in-body is intentional). Wired into `pnpm check:duplicate-brand-title` (manual). Sister scc v13.2505 same-push.
// 14.805 — 🛡️ HSTS hardening: explicit `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload` header set in next.config.ts. /loop tick 26 cross-stack HSTS audit found glw + scc were the lone outliers across the 6-site stack — Vercel's default HSTS only emits `max-age=63072000` without the includeSubDomains or preload directives, while GW + cannagent + sureel + vrg all already serve the full directive set. The directive in isolation costs nothing if we don't submit to the hstspreload.org list — it just CLAIMS the site is preload-ready. Locks subdomains under HSTS too (any future *.greenlifecannabis.com automatically gets HTTPS-only enforcement). Doug-action queue: submit greenlifecannabis.com at hstspreload.org when ready (hard-to-reverse — ≥6mo delist). Sister scc v13.2405 same-push.
