// 10.505 — 🩹 robots.txt vs sitemap.xml drift fix — `/alumni` was in BOTH `disallow` (robots.ts) AND `sitemap.ts` (added v9.905 with explicit reasoning *"Google never crawled it → 'Green Life Cannabis alumni' wouldn't surface the page in search → SEO loss for alumni discovery"*). Robots.txt wins over sitemap, so v9.905's intent (alumni discovery) was being silently undermined — Google saw the sitemap entry, fetched robots.txt, saw `Disallow: /alumni`, and skipped the page anyway. v9.905 was the more recent intent (the older `disallow` line predated the alumni-SEO ship). Removed `/alumni` from disallow array; updated comment block to reference v9.905's reasoning. Net effect: alumni page is now actually crawlable + indexable per the original v9.905 intent. Caught by /loop saturation grind 2026-05-09 cross-stack robots.txt comparison. tsc clean.
// 10.305 — 🛡️ saveCart() iOS-Safari-private wrap — `app/order/OrderMenu.tsx:66-74` `saveCart()` was calling `localStorage.setItem("gl_cart", JSON.stringify(payload))` UNWRAPPED. Sister of inv v363.005/v368.405 + scc v11.205 + this push's scc v11.305 sister. iOS Safari private mode + iOS quota-exceeded both throw on setItem; the throw bubbled out of `saveCart()` (called from cart-mutation handlers) into the React click handler → error boundary trip → cart UI tanked mid-add. The READ side `loadCart()` at line 56-64 was already wrapped; this was the missing WRITE-side sister. Worst-case impact: customer adds 5 items, switches tab, comes back, cart empty AND first add error-boundary-trips. Audit lens (`grep -rEn 'localStorage\\.(setItem|removeItem)' app components lib --include='*.tsx' --include='*.ts'`) — saveCart was the lone outlier; AgeGate / InstallAppBanner / TownCardLink / recently-viewed / stash all already wrapped. tsc clean.
// 9.905 — 🔍 SEO gap fix — `/alumni` page existed but wasn't in `app/sitemap.ts` → Google never crawled it → "Green Life Cannabis alumni" wouldn't surface the page in search. Added entry next to `/community` (monthly changefreq, priority 0.6 matching peer pages). Wenatchee-specific per memory `project_alumni_self_serve`. Caught by /loop saturation grind 2026-05-09 sitemap-coverage audit (compared `find app -name "page.tsx"` vs sitemap entries — flagged /alumni as 200-but-not-indexed; /stash legitimately noindex'd; /sign-in + /sign-up are Clerk routes that don't need sitemap entries; /order + /quiz/unsubscribe are email-link surfaces). tsc clean.
