// 8.305 — 🛡️ Cross-repo class fix — extracted `lib/rate-limit.ts` shared helper + adopted across all 4 public-API routes that had unbounded-Map rate limiters (/api/quiz/capture, /api/push/subscribe, /api/push/unsubscribe, /api/track-install, /api/orders). Pre-fix: each route had its own private `Map<key,{count,resetAt}>` with NO pruning of expired entries → unbounded growth on long-lived Vercel Fluid Compute instances. These are public endpoints (cellular IPs rotate frequently) so a 24h instance lifetime could accumulate ~10K stale entries (~500KB) before falling out. Helper opportunistically prunes (1% probability per call, O(n) bounded amortised cost). Sister: `Inventory App/src/lib/rate-limit.ts` (v345.805 + v346.205 there, 17 routes) + scc same wave (this push). 3-repo class coverage now closed. Audit: `grep 'new Map<string, { count: number; resetAt: number }>' app lib | wc -l` returns 0. tsc clean.
// 8.125 — 🛡️ Security header — `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin` restored. The lone remaining 2026-05-01-removed header (X-Frame-Options came back v8.025; nosniff was kept; HSTS auto-injected by Vercel). Pre-fix the customer surface had NO Referrer-Policy → default browser behavior leaked full URL+query to external image hosts / analytics on every cross-origin request → /loyalty?token=… / /quiz?session=… / any session-token-bearing query param could surface in third-party referer logs. Why safe vs iHJ Boost: Referrer-Policy controls OUTBOUND referer header only; Boost's inbound trust-token redemption is Permissions-Policy gated (already in place). Already shipping on inv (next.config.ts SECURITY_HEADERS) + GW + cannagent — closes the cross-site drift caught by /loop saturation grind 2026-05-09 security-header audit. Sister scc v9.345 same fix. tsc + lint clean.
// 8.105 — 🔍 SEO fix — `/apply` canonical was incorrectly pointing at `/` (homepage). Pre-fix `<link rel="canonical">` on /apply rendered as `https://www.greenlifecannabis.com` instead of `https://www.greenlifecannabis.com/apply` because `app/apply/page.tsx` is a client component (`"use client"` for the multi-step form state) — Next 16 client components can't export `metadata`, so the page silently inherited the root layout's canonical (`/`). Google then treated /apply as a duplicate of homepage and refused to index it as a separate page — anyone Googling "Green Life Cannabis apply for job" would not find /apply in search results, real SEO loss for hiring funnel. Fix: added `app/apply/layout.tsx` (server component) with proper metadata + `alternates: { canonical: "/apply" }` + Open Graph + Twitter cards. Layout wraps the client-component page.tsx without forcing it to convert. Sister scc v9.305 same fix. /careers (sister page) was already correct because page.tsx is a server component there. Caught by /loop saturation grind 2026-05-09 canonical-URL audit. Audit recipe: `for path in /apply /careers /menu /near/chelan /find-your-strain /deals; do canonical=$(curl -sL https://www.greenlifecannabis.com$path | grep -oE '<link[^>]*rel="canonical"[^>]*' | head -1 | grep -oE 'href="[^"]+"'); echo "$path → $canonical"; done` — flag any canonical that doesn't match the actual URL path. tsc + lint clean.
// 8.085 — 🚨 SEO RECOVERY — `/learn` was server-rendering ZERO content. `await auth()` from Clerk + `await getCompletedSteps(userId)` in the page component triggered Next 16's BAILOUT_TO_CLIENT_SIDE_RENDERING signal — the SSR HTML `<main>` carried only the root `app/loading.tsx` spinner ("Loading…") + a `<template data-dgst="119128617">` CSR-bailout marker. Confirmed via `curl https://www.greenlifecannabis.com/learn | grep -c '<h1'` → 0; same on Googlebot UA. Means the entire `/learn` topic list, hero h1 ("The basics, no jargon."), JSON-LD LearningResource + BreadcrumbList, and disclaimer were INVISIBLE to Google + AI crawlers. Page would slowly de-rank as a soft-404. **Fix**: extracted `await auth()` + `getCompletedSteps()` into a child Server Component `<UserStateAwareLearn>` wrapped in `<Suspense fallback={<SignedOutLearn />}>`. `<SignedOutLearn>` renders the same topic list + content as the signed-out user view, so the SSR shell ALWAYS carries the full content even before Clerk's auth resolves. `getCompletedSteps()` also got a `.catch(() => new Set())` so a DB blip doesn't blank the page. Hydration replaces the fallback with the real auth-state-aware view. Same SEO recovery pattern as glw v7.965 /apply Suspense skeleton fix. **Audit recipe** (added in code comment): `for url in $(curl <site>/sitemap.xml | grep -oE 'loc>[^<]+'); do c=$(curl -fsS $url | grep -c '<h1'); [ \"$c\" = \"0\" ] && echo \"BAILOUT $url\"; done` — flag any sitemap URL that SSR-renders zero h1, indicating likely client-bailout. Sister scc /learn next push. tsc clean.
// 8.065 — 📱 Public-site UX — iOS autofill + keyboard-hint sweep on customer + vendor forms. (1) `app/vendor-access/VendorAccessForm.tsx` Field wrapper now auto-derives `autoComplete` + `inputMode` from `type` (`type=email`→email, `type=tel`→tel) — single SSoT-style edit at the wrapper, sister of inv SettingsForm v319.805. Catches both Field calls (vendor email + phone) plus future ones. (2) `app/account/profile/ProfileForm.tsx` direct `<input>` Name + Phone — added `autoComplete=name` + `autoComplete=tel inputMode=tel`. iOS now offers contact-card autofill for these fields. (3) `app/menu/MenuSearch.tsx` search input — added the iOS code-entry trio (`autoCorrect=off autoCapitalize=off spellCheck=false`) + `enterKeyHint=search`. Customers searching "GSC" or "OG" don't get auto-corrected to "GSC's" or "Og". Sister-pattern to inv v322.405 + v323.405 staff-side sweep (now 11 surfaces total across staff + customer side use the trio + enterKeyHint). tsc clean.
// 8.045 — 🩹 Lint cleanup — 4 unescaped apostrophes on `/near` + `/near/[town]` blocking `pnpm lint`. JSX `react/no-unescaped-entities` rule flags raw `'` inside text content. Sites: (1) /near/[town]/page.tsx:173 "We're at" (2) :182 "we'll have it pulled" (3) /near/page.tsx:119 "Don't see your town?" (4) :121 "If you're driving in". All 4 swapped to `&apos;`. Pre-fix `pnpm lint` failed (4 errors); post-fix clean. Sister scc v9.265 (same /near + /near/[town] pages). Caught by /loop saturation grind iteration 65 audit recipe: just run `pnpm lint` periodically — sister of `pnpm test:all` recipe (both are baseline regression detectors that pre-commit hooks should catch but didn't). tsc + lint clean.
// 8.025 — 🔁 Redirect-chain flatten — `/book` + `/book-now` were chaining 308 → /order → 307 /menu (3 hops total). Pre-fix shipped at v7.865 forwarded to /order on the assumption that /order would eventually become the canonical product surface (when iHJ Boost is replaced by the native /order). Reality: that's months/years away (or never). The 3-hop chain was costing extra Google crawl cycles + customer latency on every clicked legacy link. Now /book + /book-now → /menu direct (single hop). When the native /order replaces iHJ, this map gets updated as a wave alongside the proxy.ts /order rewrite removal. Sister scc v9.225. Audit recipe: `for path in /book /book-now /buy /cart /pickup; do hops=$(curl -sIL <site>$path | grep -c "^HTTP/"); echo "$path hops=$hops"; done` — flag any chain >2. tsc clean.
// 8.005 — 🔍 /brands/[slug] soft-404 mitigation — generateMetadata returned `{}` (no robots hint) when brand-not-found, so the ISR-cached not-found.tsx body served at HTTP 200 could be indexed by Google as a real brand entry. Now returns `{ robots: { index: false, follow: false } }` on not-found. Sister fix to /near/[town] dynamicParams=false (v7.985, applicable for static-list routes) — brands can't use dynamicParams=false because the active-brands list is ISR-dynamic (changes as brands come/go). The noindex hint is the right defense for this dynamic-list shape. /deals/[id] already noindex on not-found (line 33). Sister scc v9.205. Single-block edit; tsc clean. Audit recipe: `for slug in /brands/totally-fake; do code=$(curl -sI <site>$slug | head -1); echo "$slug $code"; done` — confirms 200 (Next 16 quirk; can't avoid status without dynamicParams) AND `<meta name="robots" content="noindex">` (the actual Google-side defense).
// 7.985 — 🔍 /near/[town] soft-404 fix — added `export const dynamicParams = false`. Pre-fix, requests for /near/wenatchee (home-city slug not in NEAR_TOWNS) + /near/seattle (cross-store) returned HTTP 200 with `<title>Not found | Green Life Cannabis</title>` — soft-404 (200 status, not-found content). Google demotes soft-404s + a customer in our home city typing /near/wenatchee saw "Not found" instead of being routed to the relevant page. Caught by /loop saturation grind h1-count audit (returned h1=0 on these slugs). With `dynamicParams = false` + the existing `generateStaticParams` returning the canonical NEAR_TOWNS slugs, any unknown slug now triggers Next's built-in 404.tsx render with proper HTTP 404 status. Sister scc v9.185. Audit recipe: `curl -sI <site>/near/<slug-not-in-NEAR_TOWNS>` should return 404 not 200. tsc clean.
// 7.965 — ♿ /apply Suspense skeleton now ships an h1 + page-header in the SSR HTML — caught by /loop saturation grind h1-count audit. Pre-fix: `ApplyPage` wrapped `<ApplyForm />` in `<Suspense fallback={<ApplyFormSkeleton/>}>` (Next 16 forces this when ApplyForm uses `useSearchParams()` for the position deep-link). The skeleton was ONLY "Loading application form…" + a `<main>` — no h1 — so initial SSR HTML (what crawlers + Lighthouse + screen-readers see before client hydration) had ZERO h1 tags on the entire /apply page. The h1 inside ApplyForm only rendered post-hydration. Now the skeleton carries the same hero block as the form (eyebrow `Careers` + h1 `Apply to work with us`) so document-landmark is correct in SSR + no layout jump on hydration. Sister scc v9.165. Audit recipe: `for path in /; do count=$(curl -fsS https://$site$path | grep -oE "<h1\\b" | wc -l); echo "$path: h1=$count"; done` — flags pages with 0 or >1 h1 in initial HTML. tsc clean.
// 7.945 — 🔁 Legacy redirect mirror — 4 e-commerce-platform URL patterns added: `/cart` `/buy` `/pickup` `/preroll`. Pre-fix all 4 returned 404 on glw + scc. /cart + /buy are universal Shopify/WooCommerce legacy aliases (most ecommerce platforms emit one or both as default cart/checkout URLs); /pickup is a customer-intent URL some loyalty/POS platforms (SpringBig export, Dutchie public-listing, etc.) emit on legacy partner-directory pages; /preroll is the singular sister of the already-mapped /prerolls (Doug 2026-05-07 mapping). All 308 → /menu (canonical product surface). Catches stale Google index entries + bookmark URLs from prior iHeartJane / WordPress / Dutchie public-page exposures. Sister scc v9.145. Verified pre-fix 404 + post-fix 308 path on each. Single redirect-block addition; tsc clean.
// 7.925 — 🔒 Privacy-noindex two-layer defense closure on `/alumni`. Page is a Client Component (uses `useState`/`useMemo` for the secret-prompt UI + alumni-table render) so it can't export `metadata`. Pre-fix /alumni had ONLY the robots.txt Disallow — but Google sometimes indexes-despite-disallow on heavily-linked pages, and an indexed /alumni would expose the legacy team roster + the deliberately-vague secret-prompt to the SERP. New `app/alumni/layout.tsx` backfills the metadata.robots declaration as `{ index: false, follow: false }` (follow=false because nothing on the page is meant for crawlers either way). Page renders unchanged — layouts cascade metadata onto child Client Components without forcing them to be Server. Sister of `/dev` + `/devmenu` two-layer defense pattern (those are Server Components so they declare robots: noindex inline). Class hunt recipe: `for f in $(find app -name page.tsx); do is_client=$(head -3 $f | grep -c "use client"); is_disallowed=$(grep $(dirname $f | sed "s|^app||") public/robots.txt 2>/dev/null | grep -c Disallow); has_layout=$([ -f $(dirname $f)/layout.tsx ] && echo 1 || echo 0); ...`. tsc clean.
// 7.905 — 🛡️ Rate-limit on `/api/push/subscribe` POST — sister of v7.885 unsubscribe fix. Pre-fix anon-or-Clerk-OK POST ran INSERT into push_subscriptions on every call. `auth()` is optional (returns userId or null) so anonymous browsers reach the upsert. The endpoint+keys upsert dedupes on endpoint URL but a script rotating random fake endpoints+keys could balloon push_subscriptions table size + cron-fanout cost (each row gets a webpush call on every audience push). Now: 10/min/IP in-memory Map, identical pattern to /api/push/unsubscribe (v7.885) + /api/track-install + /api/quiz/capture in this repo. 429 + Retry-After: 60 on cap. Sister scc v9.025 same fix. tsc clean.
// 7.885 — 🛡️ Rate-limit on `/api/push/unsubscribe` POST — gap caught by audit recipe `for f in $(find app/api -name "route.ts"); do has_post=...; has_rate=...; has_auth=...; ...`. Pre-fix anon POST ran a DB DELETE against push_subscriptions on a 1024-char endpoint string with NO rate-limit. Scripted attacker with captured endpoint URLs (leaked via browser DevTools on a victim's device) could mass-unsubscribe + spam-call to bog DB index probe + bloat Vercel logs. Now: 10/min/IP in-memory Map, identical pattern to /api/track-install + /api/quiz/capture in this repo. 429 + Retry-After: 60 on cap. Sister scc v8.985 same fix. tsc clean.
