// 7.195 — 🚨 SOFT-404 fix: /blog/[slug] + /heroes/[cohort] now return real 404 for unknown slugs (was 200-with-not-found-content). Sister of scc v8.335. Caught while verifying new posts render — `curl /blog/nonexistent-test-slug-12345` returned 200 instead of 404. Body contained &ldquo;404&rdquo; + &ldquo;not found&rdquo; text but HTTP status was 200 (Next.js 16 default with `dynamicParams=true` + statically-generated routes). **SEO impact**: Google distinguishes real 404 from soft-404 (200-with-error-content); soft 404s erode adjacent paths' authority signal — every WP-era legacy URL not yet ported as a real post would have been categorized as soft-404 (200 + &ldquo;not found&rdquo; text → Google sees thin/error page on a real URL → de-indexes adjacent paths). Fix: added `export const dynamicParams = false;` to both `/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` + `/heroes/[cohort]/page.tsx` — only slugs from generateStaticParams() are served, all others return clean 404. /brands/[slug] LEFT alone (DB-backed dynamic — would break new-brand discovery). tsc clean. Verification next deploy: `curl -fsS -o /dev/null -w &quot;%{http_code}&quot; /blog/nonexistent-test-slug-12345` should return 404 (was 200).
