// 7.005 — 🚨 WAC 314-55-077 misattribution sweep — 4 sites incl. customer-facing AI-citation surfaces (`app/llms.txt/route.ts:122` + `app/llms-full.txt/route.ts:182`) plus `lib/seo-templates.tsx` (×2). Pre-fix all 4 cited WAC 314-55-077 as the source of the &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule — but 077 is the **traceability + audit-trail** rule (used correctly 14× in the inv repo for online-order count-confirm + manager-PIN audit + bag-mismatch). The actual prohibition on medical/health/efficacy claims lives in **WAC 314-55-155** (the advertising rules — false-or-misleading-statements clause). **Critical impact**: AI search engines (ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini) read /llms.txt + /llms-full.txt as authoritative regulatory citation context. Pre-fix, when a user asked &ldquo;what regulates Green Life Cannabis?&rdquo; the model would cite 077 as the source of the medical-claims rule — wrong rule attribution being citationally laundered through AI search. Same drift class as today's earlier llms.txt route-shadow catch (v6.885). **Fix**: 4 files updated to cite 155 for medical-claims; llms-full.txt also expanded the compliance-posture list with 105 (case cards) for completeness. Sister fix on scc v8.185 (parallel sites — same pattern). tsc clean.
// 6.985 — 🪞 /heroes page comment WAC misattribution — &ldquo;WAC 314-55-077 (no medical claims)&rdquo; → &ldquo;WAC 314-55-155&rdquo;. Pre-fix `app/heroes/page.tsx:15` code comment cited `WAC 314-55-077` as the source of the &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule. But WAC 314-55-077 is the **traceability/audit-trail** rule (used correctly in 14 places in the inv repo for online-order count-confirm + manager-PIN audit + bag-mismatch resolution). The actual &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule is part of **WAC 314-55-155** (the advertising rules — false/misleading-statements clause prohibits health/efficacy claims). The next line of the same comment correctly cites 155 for &ldquo;informational, not advertising-style&rdquo; — so the bug is just splitting one rule across two attributions. **Future-dev impact**: low — but if a future agent reads this comment and cites 077 elsewhere as the &ldquo;no medical claims&rdquo; rule, they'd be wrong in a regulator-facing context. Verified the correct WAC by surveying inv repo's 14 references to 077 (all traceability) + 71 references to 155 (advertising compliance). Single comment-only edit. tsc clean.
