// 6.885 — 🪦 Deleted dead-shadowed `public/llms.txt` (3KB static file). Major drift catch: `app/llms.txt/route.ts` (added v3.56 in the AI-search Phase 2 push) has been silently shadowing `public/llms.txt` (added in the original `c8afa77 GEO: beefed-up LocalBusiness schema` commit) for months — Next.js App Router serves `app/[file].txt/route.ts` over `public/[file].txt` at the same path. Verified via `diff <(curl /llms.txt) public/llms.txt` — completely different content (route has structured Quick-facts list; static had a single paragraph). My v6.805 &ldquo;fix&rdquo; to `public/llms.txt` (`413490 → 414755` + `veteran-owned → locally owned`) was a no-op — AI search engines see the route output, not the static file. Future agents reading `public/llms.txt` and finding drift will keep &ldquo;fixing&rdquo; a file that nobody serves. The route handler at `app/llms.txt/route.ts` is the SSoT — already has correct license + correct brand-voice + correct shop URL. Pinned a memory `feedback_llms_txt_route_shadows_static` so this doesn't happen again. Sister deletion on scc v8.125 (same dead-shadow pattern there). 1 file removed per repo.
