// 5.585 — 🐛 /faq Q "Can I redeem loyalty points on top of a deal?" had a stale "online 20%" reference — Wen's online discount is 15% (per /sign-up, /llms.txt, /deals OG card, all other surfaces). Sister of scc v6.665 — same drift class on both stores. Fix: "online 20%" → "online 15%". Customer-facing copy across Wen now consistent at 15%.
// 5.465 — 🐛 /llms-full.txt no-stacking copy fix — Q&A about deals/loyalty was saying "The 15% off first online order applies on top of any active deal" which directly contradicts Doug's 2026-05-07 no-stacking policy (memory `feedback_no_stacking_ever`). The /llms-full.txt is the AI-search corpus that ChatGPT/Claude search/Perplexity load when citing the store; the wrong copy would propagate as misinformation across every AI-search surface. Replaced with "Discounts don't combine — best discount applies. Loyalty points still earn on every visit regardless of which discount is in play." Same drift class as v4.945's no-stacking sweep across the visible pages — this one was the missed-mirror in the LLM corpus. Sister: scc same wave. tsc clean.
// 5.425 — 🚨 Homepage FAQ address fix — Q1 ('Where is the best dispensary in Wenatchee?') was answering with a WRONG street + number: "3001 N Sunnyslope Rd". Canonical address per `lib/store.ts` + `STORE_LAYOUT_WENATCHEE.md` + 4 other docs is "3012 Center Road Ste A, Wenatchee, WA 98801". Sunnyslope is the NEIGHBORHOOD, not the street name. Pre-fix this FAQ Q&A is high-leverage SEO content — it's both visible to customers AND emitted as `@type: Question` / `@type: Answer` JSON-LD that AI Overviews / ChatGPT / Perplexity / Google rich-results all pull verbatim. Risk: an AI engine confidently telling customers to drive to a non-existent address. Fix: aligned to canonical "3012 Center Road Ste A in Wenatchee — the Sunnyslope side of town" so the neighborhood reference stays for the geo-anchor while the actual street + number are correct. Single-line copy fix; FAQPage JSON-LD payload regenerates from this string at next render. tsc clean.
// 5.385 — /accessibility WEB_A11Y_NOTES expanded — adds 2 new claims documenting the v5.025 (focus indicator / WCAG 2.4.7) + v5.065 (loading-state announcements / WCAG 4.1.3) ADA ships. Pre-existing notes still accurate; new claims align legal-cover statement with implementation. ADA Title III defensive copy. Sister: scc v6.505.
// 5.265 — 🛡️ `/api/push/unsubscribe` adds 1024-char endpoint length cap — symmetric with `/api/push/subscribe`'s existing cap. Defense-in-depth: without the cap, a malicious caller could send a multi-MB endpoint string that bogs down the DELETE query's index probe + bloats Vercel response logs. Subscribe already capped at 1024 (length 1024 / p256dh 256 / auth 64 — the natural sizes for a Web Push API endpoint); unsubscribe inherited none of those checks because the route was a thinner DELETE-by-endpoint with no upsert validation. Sister mirror on scc v6.385. Single-file edit per repo, ~5 LOC. tsc clean.
// 5.185 — 🛡️ `/api/push/send` Bearer-token compare uses `crypto.timingSafeEqual` instead of `===`. Auth-class hardening sister to scc v6.105 + inv v186.845. Pre-fix `authz !== expected` short-circuits on first differing byte — measurable timing side-channel proportional to how many leading characters of `PUSH_SEND_TOKEN` an attacker has correctly guessed. Practical risk small (PUSH_SEND_TOKEN is admin-curated + rotates if compromised + the worst-case impact of a stolen token is sending unauthorized push notifications to subscribed customers, not customer-data leakage), but the rest of the codebase already uses timing-safe compare for all secret-equality checks (`verifyBearer` in inv lib/cron-bearer.ts, `verifyOtp` in inv lib/auth.ts, scc lib/rewards-session.ts). Imports `timingSafeEqual` from `node:crypto`, length-mismatch short-circuits before the constant-time compare. Sister mirror on scc same wave. Single-file edit per repo. tsc clean.
// 5.105 — `/api/track-install` no longer writes `customers.scc_app_installed_at` on Wen — semantic-cleanup of cross-store column drift. The column is Sea-named (introduced via inventoryapp migration 0215 to power the Seattle SpringBig→SCC migration funnel tile at /admin/marketing) and Wen has no equivalent admin tile reading it — but the Wen track-install endpoint was writing to it on every Clerk-authed install. Functionally harmless (column exists on both Neons via shared migration; data was just never read on Wen) but semantically wrong + would confuse future agents. Net cleanup: remove the UPDATE on Wen-side; audit_log row at action='glw.pwa_installed' remains the canonical source of truth for Wen install counts. If a Wen-side customer-table install column is ever needed, add `glw_app_installed_at` first. tsc clean.
// 5.065 — ADA accessibility round 3 — root loading.tsx Suspense fallback announces to screen readers (WCAG 4.1.3 Status Messages). Pre-fix the customer-side spinner had no role=status / aria-live / aria-busy — users with screen readers heard NOTHING during the loading state. Adds the three ARIA attributes + aria-hidden on the decorative spinner div so screen readers announce just the visible "Loading…" text once. Sister: scc v5.915 + inv v186.765.
// 5.025 — ADA accessibility round 2 — global :focus-visible safety-net ring (WCAG 2.4.7). Most components have explicit Tailwind `focus-visible:ring-...` classes already, but a few legacy/library buttons inherited `focus:outline-none` from a parent without painting their own ring — keyboard-only users had no visible focus indicator on those, breaking WCAG 2.4.7 (Focus Visible). Single global rule paints a 2px green-600 outline on any `:focus-visible` element that didn't already get a custom ring. `:focus-visible` only matches keyboard focus, so mouse clicks don't flicker. Components that already paint a custom ring can opt out via `no-default-focus` class. Sister: scc v5.875. Single CSS edit covers all interactive elements site-wide.
// 4.985 — ADA accessibility round 1 — globals.css honors prefers-reduced-motion: reduce. Pre-fix ~20 customer-facing sites used animate-pulse/spin/bounce without a motion-reduce: Tailwind variant — users with vestibular conditions / migraine triggers / motion sensitivity saw all animations regardless of their OS pref (WCAG 2.3.3 / SC-2.3.3 requirement). Blanket CSS override slows ALL animations + transitions to near-static (0.01ms) when the OS pref is set + explicit animation: none on common Tailwind motion classes. Sister: scc v5.745. Single CSS edit covers ~20 sites without per-component refactors. Doug 2026-05-07 ADA pass.
// 4.835 — `/menu` + `MenuFallback` close-time copy now reads today's hours instead of `STORE.hours[0]?.close`. Pre-fix the `Pickup orders open daily 8 AM–{STORE.hours[0]?.close ?? "9 PM"}` line on `/menu` and the matching MenuFallback footer copy always returned Monday's close (9 PM) — so on Friday and Saturday, when Wen actually closes at 10 PM, customers landing on `/menu` saw a 1-hour-too-early close time. v4.315 fixed the SSoT (Fri/Sat 11pm → 10pm) plus 3 fallbacks (OG card, /our-story, /faq) but missed `/menu` + `MenuFallback`. Fix: new `todayCloseLabel()` helper in `lib/store.ts` that finds today's row by `todayDay()` (TZ-aware via `STORE_TZ`) — page is ISR 60s so the value stays fresh through the day. Sister mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v5.715 (defensive — Sea is uniform 11 PM today so no current visible drift, but adopting the same helper now prevents regressions if Sea adds Fri/Sat hours later). tsc clean.
// 4.825 — /treasure-chest added to sitemap. Surface shipped v4.385 + linked from /menu strip + homepage pill, but `app/sitemap.ts` was never updated — meaning Google has never crawl-discovered the clearance lane. Pre-fix only customers who navigated the homepage pill OR the /menu strip ever saw it. Adding to sitemap with daily changeFrequency (inventory turns) + 0.7 priority (less than /deals which is the primary commerce surface, more than /faq). Sister: scc v5.665. tsc clean. 1 file, 1 entry added.
// 4.745 — /menu page now respects PWA install cookie for app-only deals — closes the install-incentive gap on the most-visited customer page. Pre-fix /menu called getActiveDeals() without args, so installed visitors saw the same `app_only=false` subset as browser-only visitors — losing the install incentive on the deals strip Doug spent the v4.495+ work setting up. Fix: read `glw_pwa_installed` cookie, pass `includeAppOnly` to getActiveDeals (matches /deals + homepage strip pattern). 4-surface coverage now complete: /deals list, /deals/[id] deep page (v4.705), homepage strip, /menu strip. Sister: scc v5.625. tsc clean.
// 4.705 — /deals/[id] gates app-only deals on PWA install — sister to scc v5.605. Same SMS-share leak: getDealById SQL didn't query app_only column; hardcoded appOnly: false. Customer shares /deals/<app-only-id> via SMS, recipient (browser-only) views full discount + landing page, bypasses the install incentive. Fix: getDealById SELECTs COALESCE(app_only, FALSE) + returns it; page + generateMetadata both check glw_pwa_installed cookie + 404 when appOnly && !installed. tsc clean.
// 4.625 — **`cross_store_promo` slot mounted on homepage between brands and FAQ.** Closes the loop on Doug 2026-05-07 ask: "we cross advertise on each others sites since we cant exchange money." Slot was added to PLACEMENT_SLOTS (inv v180.345) + admin form picker, but the public-site mount was missing — Doug could create cross-store ads but they'd never render. Now mounted in a dedicated section between the homepage_under_brands slot and the FAQ. VendorAdSlot returns null when no active ad in the slot, so invisible until Doug curates an entry. Mirror on scc v5.545. tsc clean.
// 4.595 — **InstallAppBanner copy refresh — leads with "App-only deals."** Mirror of scc v5.265. Old: "Order faster, see your rewards, get drop notifications." New: "App-only deals · your rewards · drop notifications · faster ordering." App-only deals leads since it's the strongest install incentive — pairs with the v4.495 app-only-deals filter that's now live on /deals + /menu deals strip + homepage deals strip. Symmetry with Sea + closes the copy-asymmetry between the two stores' install banners. Single-line fix.
// 4.575 — **Homepage Today's-deals strip respects the app-install cookie.** v4.495 added the cookie + filter on /deals; homepage was rendering the full deals list (incl `app_only=true`) unconditionally — leaking app-only deals to non-installed visitors via the homepage strip. Now reads `glw_pwa_installed` cookie via Next 16 `cookies()` + passes `includeAppOnly={isInstalled}` to `getActiveDeals()`. Symmetry with /deals page. Mirror on scc v5.425. tsc clean.
// 4.555 — **3 new VendorAdSlot mounts on glw — `menu_top`, `deals_page_top`, `treasure_chest_top`.** Pairs with inv v180.345 enum extension. Doug 2026-05-07: more display-ad slots so we can advertise certain vendors + cross-promote (no money exchange — reciprocal placements). Each mount is a 1-line `<VendorAdSlot slot="..." />` near the top of the page; existing component returns null when no active ads, so pages don't need any gate-checks. Slots become curatable on /admin/marketing/vendor-ads once inv v180.345 deploys. tsc clean. 3 files.
// 4.535 — **STORE_TZ SSoT arc — `lib/store.ts` now exports a canonical `STORE_TZ` constant; ~14 inline `"America/Los_Angeles"` literals across 12 consumers migrated to import it.** Sister of inventoryapp's `STORE_TZ` arc closed at v167.665. **Ships:** (1) `lib/store.ts` exports `STORE_TZ`; the existing internal `const TZ` aliases it (no behavior change). (2) Inline literals migrated in: `app/page.tsx`, `app/order/confirmation/[id]/page.tsx`, `app/contact/page.tsx`, `app/about/page.tsx`, `app/visit/page.tsx`, `app/deals/page.tsx`, `app/api/orders/route.ts`, `app/account/page.tsx`, `app/account/orders/page.tsx`, `components/AnnouncementBar.tsx`, `components/MobileStickyCta.tsx`, `lib/deal-countdown.ts`. **Why this matters:** five Doug-only stores under one DST switch is fine, but the inline pattern is the same drift-class as the IS_SEATTLE arc and the storeToday() arc — any future cross-store rollout (Spokane, Bellingham, etc.) would have to touch every file rather than one constant. Closing now while the surface is small. **Verification:** `grep -rn '"America/Los_Angeles"' --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"` matches only the SSoT line in `lib/store.ts`. **Sister still open:** seattle-cannabis-web has the same ~14 inline sites + a sister `lib/store.ts` — closes in next push to keep diffs small. tsc clean.
// 4.495 — **App-only deals filter + /api/track-install mirrored from scc.** Doug 2026-05-07 ask was Sea-focused but Wen needs symmetry so existing customers don't see drift between the two stores. **Ships:** (1) `app/api/track-install/route.ts` mirrored from scc v5.305 with glw_pwa_installed cookie name + `system:glw_pwa_install:v1` actor + Green Life branding. (2) `lib/db.ts` `getActiveDeals({ includeAppOnly })` — same pattern as scc. (3) `app/deals/page.tsx` reads `glw_pwa_installed` cookie + passes flag. (4) `components/InstallAppBanner.tsx` gains `recordInstall(source)` call on android-accept + ios-sheet-open + a standalone-launch path via sessionStorage sentinel. Customer flow identical to Sea — install banner → install → cookie → app-only deals visible. Pairs with inv v179.785 (deals.app_only schema) which deploys to both stores' Neon. tsc clean. 4 files.
// 4.475 — **/menu deals strip surfaces a Treasure-chest chip when clearance lane has items.** Sister to v4.415 homepage pill. Pre-fix /treasure-chest was reachable from `/` only — customers landing directly on /menu had no path to the clearance lane. **Ships:** (1) `MenuActiveDealsStrip` accepts new optional `treasureChestCount` prop. (2) Render gate flips from "deals empty → null" to "deals OR treasure empty → null" so a clearance-only state still surfaces. (3) Heading text adapts: "Live deals · N running" when deals exist, "Clearance lane" when only treasure does. (4) Amber Treasure chip prepends the deals row with `🪙 Treasure · N on clearance` label, attribution-tagged via `withAttr` for menu→treasure conversion tracking. /menu page passes `getTreasureChestProducts(60).length` to the strip. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v5.105. tsc clean.
// 4.445 — **Hotfix — SELECT + RETURNING in lib/portal.ts now actually include `email_opt_in` and `frequency_pref` columns.** v4.395 (email opt-in) + v4.435 (frequency tier) both updated PortalUser type + mapPortalUser to read these columns, but the underlying SQL SELECT in getOrCreatePortalUserWithCreated was never updated to fetch them. Result: every portal user load returned default values for both fields regardless of what was in the DB — toggle on /account/profile saved correctly but never read back. Fix: add `pu.email_opt_in, pu.frequency_pref` to the SELECT column list + same to the INSERT RETURNING. mapPortalUser fallbacks already handle missing columns so no migration order dependency. tsc clean. 1 file edit.
// 4.435 — **Install-app banner + frequency-tier selector — Doug 2026-05-07 launch playbook step 1.** Pushes the PWA install on mobile + lets customers opt into more (or fewer) marketing texts. **NEW component** `components/InstallAppBanner.tsx` — fixed-bottom mobile-only banner, hidden when running standalone (already installed) or after dismiss (30-day cool-down via localStorage). Android: captures `beforeinstallprompt` event + fires on tap. iOS Safari: opens a step-by-step Share → Add-to-Home-Screen sheet (no native prompt API exists). Mounted in `app/layout.tsx` so it renders on every customer-facing page on mobile only. **Frequency-tier selector on /account/profile:** 3-button grid between SMS/email opt-ins and the No-Substitutions toggle — 'Just essentials' (≤2/mo) · 'Standard' (≤4/mo, default) · 'More updates' (≤8/mo). Persists via the existing `/api/profile` POST. **Plumbing** (sister to v4.395 email-opt-in pattern): `lib/portal.ts` PortalUser type adds `frequencyPref`; mapPortalUser reads `frequency_pref`; updatePortalUser COALESCEs the new field; `app/api/profile/route.ts` POST validates the enum value. **Migration:** depends on inventoryapp v177.325 (`0213_portal_users_frequency_pref.sql`). tsc clean. 1 new component + 4 file edits.
// 4.415 — **Homepage Today's-deals strip surfaces /treasure-chest pill when chest has products.** /treasure-chest was unreachable from any nav link. Customers wouldn't find it unless they typed the URL. Fix: the existing "Today's deals" header strip on `/` already has an "All deals →" link in the corner; added a sibling `🪙 Treasure chest · {N}` amber pill alongside, server-rendered conditionally on `getTreasureChestProducts(60).length > 0` so we don't show an empty pill. Same gate as the deals strip itself (only renders when there's something live), so the placement reuses an already-conditional surface. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v5.075. **Edge case noted (not handled in v0):** if `deals.length === 0` but `treasureChestCount > 0`, the deals section won't render at all per existing gate, so the pill won't show either. Acceptable for v0 — clearance lane is empty more often than the deals lane is empty in practice. tsc clean.
