// 4.385 — **NEW /treasure-chest customer-facing surface — mirrors `/admin/treasure-chest` curation lane.** Doug 2026-05-07: "build in something for treasure chest (our old slow selling items) have there be a tag to make items 'treasure chest' so its easier to display those sale items." Admin side already shipped (inventoryapp v173.605 — staff tag products with `display_priority='clearance'`). This ships the customer-visible surface. **What ships:** (1) `lib/db.ts` new `getTreasureChestProducts(limit=60)` reads `products.display_priority='clearance'` joined to `latest_inv > 0` + `brands_with_recent_sales` (same per-store carry-here gate as `/menu`). Sorted by price ASC so the cheapest deal leads. (2) `app/treasure-chest/page.tsx` new server-component page — amber theming (🪙 treasure-chest visual identity, distinct from green Loyalty / red Heroes / red Strain SAT), 5-col responsive grid, per-card 🪙 Treasure pill, friendly empty-state ("the chest is empty right now") that always falls back to /menu, "How the Treasure Chest works" footer block explaining the curation logic. force-dynamic + revalidate=0 so newly-tagged items show immediately. Mirror on seattle-cannabis-web v4.005. **Why the customer-facing copy matters:** policy is "best discount wins, never combine" — the page copy frames each item as already-discounted ("priced to move"), which avoids the customer asking "can I stack a deal on top?" Single SQL query, simple grid, no client JS. tsc clean.
