// 8.145 — 🛡️ Cross-repo port of inv v337.005 STAFF_APP_URL allow-list defense — `lib/closure-status.ts` `inventoryappBase()` was using `env && env.startsWith("https://") ? env : DEFAULT` to validate `NEXT_PUBLIC_INVENTORYAPP_URL`. Same vulnerability that broke STAFF_APP_URL on inv prod for 24h: env was set to `https://app.greenlifecannabis.com` (404'd subdomain), passed `startsWith("https://")` check, every closure-status fetch 404'd → graceful-degrade returned `{ isClosed: false }` → public site showed OPEN even when manager flagged emergency closure on brapp/admin. Customers could place orders during a real closure. Fix: allow-list requiring `hostname === "brapp.greenlifecannabis.com"`. Sister fix in scc v9.365 (same file, same shape). Sister of inv v337.005 + v338.005 + v340.605 + v340.805 cross-host base URL hardening sweep. tsc clean.
// 7.375 — 🛡️ NEW build-gate `scripts/check-site-url-defense.mjs` — pins v7.235 (welcome-email) + v7.275 (quiz-nurture-email) vercel.app-defense pattern against regression. Sister of scc v8.515 + GW v2.82.80 cross-repo arc gates. Scans `app/` + `lib/` + `components/` for inline `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL || "<canonical>"` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_ORIGIN || "<canonical>"` (without `.includes(".vercel.app")` rejection). Exempts 2 SSoT-aware files (welcome-email + quiz-nurture-email — glw lacks /rewards which scc has) + lib/version.ts (build-version pin). **Wired**: `pnpm check:site-url-defense` manual run. **Verified**: 0 offenders across 177 files. tsc clean.
// 8.165 — 🚀 sitemap.xml + robots.txt + manifest.webmanifest CDN cache (cross-repo port of inv v342.605 + v342.405 OG cache). Pre-fix all 3 metadata-route endpoints served `cache-control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate` (Next.js default). Sitemap pulls from DB (brands/deals/posts) — every Google/Bing/AI-bot crawl re-rendered + re-queried Postgres. Robots + manifest are fully static. Added `export const revalidate = 1800` (sitemap, 30-min — DB-driven balances freshness vs cache) + `revalidate = 3600` (robots + manifest, 1-hour — fully static). Sister fixes shipping in scc v9.385 + GW v2.93.05. tsc clean.
// 8.185 — 🚀 Dynamic per-slug OG image CDN cache (sister of v8.165 metadata-routes). Pre-fix `app/blog/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx` + `app/brands/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx` + `app/deals/[id]/opengraph-image.tsx` all served `cache-control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate` with `x-vercel-cache: MISS` — every social-crawler hit re-rendered Satori from scratch (~200-500ms). Per-slug OG content rarely changes (blog/brand 24h cache, deals 1h since promo terms change). Added `export const revalidate = 86400` (blog + brands) + `revalidate = 3600` (deals). Net: ~99% CDN hit rate on repeated shares. Sister fixes in scc v9.405 same shape.
// 8.205 — 🐛 v8.185 fix didn't actually work — `revalidate` export doesn't apply to ImageResponse routes. Verified post-deploy: cache-control still `max-age=0` + `x-vercel-cache: MISS` across 3 sequential hits. The pattern that DOES work (verified live on inv v342.405): set `headers: { "Cache-Control": "..." }` in the ImageResponse options object directly. Re-applied to all 3 dynamic OG files with explicit headers (24h on blog/brands, 1h on deals). Sister fix in scc v9.425 same shape. tsc clean.
// 10.005 — 🌐 Search Console + Bing Webmaster Tools + Yandex env-driven verification meta tags + GA4 gtag.js loader added to root layout. When Doug pastes `GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION` / `BING_SITE_VERIFICATION` / `YANDEX_VERIFICATION` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID` into Vercel env, each renders site-wide; empty env = nothing renders (zero bytes shipped). Sister of GW root layout pattern + scc v10.905 + cannagent. Cross-repo SEO arc 2026-05-09: env-gating means the moment Doug verifies the property in any dashboard, the meta tag goes live without another deploy. tsc clean.
// 10.105 — 🌐 Meta-description length sweep — 9 over-limit descriptions trimmed to ≤160 chars (Google SERP cap). Pages: `/` (root layout 289→151, app/page.tsx 209→155), `/learn`, `/deals`, `/about`, `/visit`, `/blog`, `/menu` 227→155, `/near` 176→150, `/our-story` 194→150, `/heroes` 179→155, `/faq` 176→150, `/find-your-strain` 292→155, `/treasure-chest` 206→150, `/brands/[slug]` 242→155. Pre-fix Google was truncating mid-sentence with "…" in SERPs. Sister of GW v2.92 + scc v11.005 length sweep. Audit recipe: `find app -name page.tsx -exec grep -E "^\\s*description:" {} \\; | awk '{ if (length > 165) print FILENAME }'`. tsc clean.
// 18.705 — 📧 List-Unsubscribe HTTP headers wired on quiz-nurture sequence (D+0/D+5/D+12). Pre-fix `lib/email.ts sendEmail()` had NO support for emitting List-Unsubscribe header — only the body-link footer existed. Per RFC 8058 + Gmail's Feb 2024 bulk-sender requirements, marketing emails benefit from `List-Unsubscribe: <URL>, <mailto:...>` + `List-Unsubscribe-Post: List-Unsubscribe=One-Click` headers — Gmail/Apple Mail/Yahoo surface a one-click Unsubscribe button at the top of the email (recipient doesn't scroll to body link), and Gmail rewards senders honoring this RFC even at low volume with better inbox placement. Added optional `unsubscribeUrl?: string` to `SendEmailArgs`; when set, sendEmail emits both headers. 3 quiz-nurture sendEmail calls now thread `unsubscribeUrl(args.unsubscribeToken)` through. Order-confirmation + welcome emails are transactional (not subject to bulk-sender rules), no change needed there. Sister of GW src/lib/email.ts SendEmailOptions.unsubscribeUrl pattern + scc v13.6405 same shape. tsc clean.
// 18.805 — 🚀 /visit page CDN cache restored — was uncached on every hit. Pre-fix `app/visit/page.tsx` declared `export const revalidate = 300` at the top, but `fetchClosureStatus()` (called inside the page body) defaults to `cache: "no-store"` per `lib/closure-status.ts:63`. Per Next 16 docs, ANY internal fetch with `cache: "no-store"` opts the whole page out of static caching — `revalidate = 300` was silently overridden. Verified pre-fix via curl: `cache-control: private, no-cache, no-store, max-age=0` + `x-vercel-cache: MISS` despite the page-level revalidate. Fix: pass `{ revalidate: 60 }` to fetchClosureStatus on /visit (sister pattern: /not-found.tsx already does this since v3.585). Page now caches at the Vercel edge for 5 min (page-level) with 60s freshness on the closure-status fetch. Customers landing pre-drive still see emergency-closure banners within ~60s. /menu + /order intentionally keep `no-store` — those need the freshest signal to block ordering during an active closure. Sister of scc v13.6505 same shape. Doug-impact: every /visit hit was spawning a new function — common path for customers checking hours/address before driving over. tsc clean.
// 18.905 — 📰 RSS 2.0 feed at /feed.xml + `<link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml">` in root layout. Pre-fix the site published 12+ blog posts with no machine-readable feed — Feedly/NewsBlur/Inoreader 404'd on /feed.xml, /rss.xml, /atom.xml; /feed → /blog 308 served HTML to feed parsers (useless); GPTBot/ClaudeBot/PerplexityBot all probe /feed.xml as a structured-content surface. New `app/feed.xml/route.ts` emits RSS 2.0 with channel meta (title, link, atom:link self-ref, description, language, lastBuildDate) + per-post `<item>` (title, link, guid as permalink, description, pubDate as RFC 822, category). Posts sorted most-recent-first per RSS convention. XML escape via 5-entity replace (&/</>/\"/'). 30-min edge cache + 1hr stale-while-revalidate (sister of sitemap.xml v8.165 cache config) — at most 30 min lag for new post to surface. Root layout `metadata.alternates.types` adds `application/rss+xml` → readers auto-discover when user pastes homepage URL. Customer + AI-crawler discoverability win on a 12+ post archive that was effectively invisible to feed-shaped consumers. tsc clean.
// 18.915 — 📰 v18.905 RSS feed self-regression caught: post-deploy curl on https://www.greenlifecannabis.com/ returned ZERO `<link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml">` in HEAD despite the route serving 200 with proper RSS body. Root cause: Next 16 metadata cascade SHALLOW-overwrites — `app/page.tsx` declared its own `alternates: { canonical: "/" }` which fully replaced the layout's `alternates.types` block. Same bug class as memory pin `feedback_og_silent_drop_class` (T7-T9 Twitter card cascade) and the per-route OG dead-code arc (T48-T50). Fix: page.tsx now also declares `types: { "application/rss+xml": ... }` so the page-level metadata wins WITH the RSS link rel intact. Layout-level kept for any other route that doesn't declare its own alternates. Verified live post-deploy. Caught via prod-headers-first methodology — the route was working but discovery wasn't. Methodology lesson: when shipping a new metadata-API surface, always re-curl the rendered HTML, not just the new route. tsc clean.
// 19.005 — 🌐 HowTo + FAQPage entity-graph @id linking on glw homepage. Pre-fix the homepage had Organization/WebSite/LocalBusiness/AggregateRating all with stable `@id` IRIs but HowTo + FAQPage were missing them — couldn't be cleanly referenced from sibling JSON-LD nodes (BreadcrumbList, Reviews) which already use @id refs. Caught by /loop tick 89 cross-stack JSON-LD validation sweep — same audit that surfaced the GW MedicalClinic gaps T83/T85/T86/T87/T88. Added `@id: ${STORE.website}/#howto-pickup` (HowTo) + `@id: ${STORE.website}/#faq` (FAQPage). Now ALL 8 JSON-LD entities on the homepage have @id IRIs, fully connected entity-graph. Sister of GW T87+T88 entity-graph @id pattern (Article, WebSite, Physician). Sister of scc v13.6705 same shape. tsc clean.
// 19.105 — 🌐 BreadcrumbList @id added on lib/breadcrumb-jsonld.ts SoT helper + 2 inline emitters (/blog/[slug] + /brands/[slug]). Pre-fix every BreadcrumbList on glw was missing entity-level `@id`, making it a dangling node — Article + SpecialAnnouncement + CollectionPage couldn't reference the breadcrumb via @id (had to inline-duplicate the path). Caught by /loop tick 91 audit on /deals/[id] + /blog/[slug]. (1) `breadcrumbJsonLd()` SoT helper now emits `@id: ${lastCrumbAbs}#breadcrumb` derived from the LAST crumb's URL (the page the breadcrumb is anchored to). All 4 callers (apply, heroes/[cohort], deals/[id], careers) inherit automatically. (2) /blog/[slug] inline schema gets `@id: ${url}#breadcrumb`. (3) /brands/[slug] inline schema gets `@id: ${brandUrl}#breadcrumb` AND a NEW middle "Brands" level (was Home → Brand directly; now Home › Brands › Brand for richer SERP path display + matches actual nav). Sister of scc v13.6805. Closes BreadcrumbList side of the entity-graph @id linking arc T85 → T87 → T88 → T89 → T90 → T91. tsc clean.
// 19.205 — 🌐 BreadcrumbList @id on /near/[town] inline schema. T91 helper-fix didn't catch this because /near/[town] uses an inline schema (T85 dead-code-helper class — pinned via memory `feedback_seo_helper_dead_code_curl_recipe.md` this tick). Caught by /loop tick 92 cross-page audit. Added `@id: ${STORE.website}/near/${slug}#breadcrumb`. Sister of scc v13.6905. tsc clean.
// 19.305 — 🌐 BreadcrumbList @id swept across 8 more glw inner pages — /our-story, /about, /faq, /learn, /heroes, /find-your-strain, /press, /deals. Each had inline schema bypassing the SoT helper. Cross-page survey via curl + JSON.parse on every page found 8 of 10 probed had MISSING @id (only /contact + /accessibility had no breadcrumb at all — separate gap not addressed this tick). Python sweep injected `@id: ${STORE.website}<path>#breadcrumb` after `"@type": "BreadcrumbList",` line on each file. The sweep validates the T92 memory pin recipe at scale: 8 inline-bypass cases caught in one shot via the "inline-bypass grep + live curl" verification step. Sister of scc v13.7005. tsc clean.
// 19.405 — 🌐 BreadcrumbList @id swept across 3 more glw inner pages — /community, /visit, /menu. Round-2 of T93 sweep — second cross-page audit caught 3 more inline-bypass cases the first probe-batch missed (different URL set probed). Same Python sweep pattern. /contact, /treasure-chest, /vendor-access, /accessibility intentionally NOT addressed — those pages emit NO BreadcrumbList at all (separate gap, lower-priority since none currently rank above /faq for navigation queries). Sister of scc v13.7105. tsc clean.
