// 19.805 — 🎨 Per-cohort OG share-cards on /heroes/[cohort] — pre-T99 all 5 cohorts (veterans/military/first-responders/healthcare/teachers) fell back to generic homepage OG when shared on social/SMS/iMessage. Page-level metadata had `images: [DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE]` explicit array which dead-coded any per-route opengraph-image.tsx file convention (T48-T50 same shallow-overwrite class). NEW `app/heroes/[cohort]/opengraph-image.tsx` reads `params.cohort` and renders cohort-themed 1200×630 PNG with cohort-label uppercase + tagline H1 + brand mark. Page-level metadata also rewired: `images: [{ url: '/heroes/{slug}/opengraph-image', ..., alt: '${label} · 30% off · ${STORE.name}' }]`. 24hr edge cache via `headers: Cache-Control` (sister of v8.205 ImageResponse cache pattern — `revalidate` doesn't apply to ImageResponse routes). 5 cohort-specific share-cards now serve. Sister of scc v13.7405. tsc clean.
// 19.905 — 🚀 T99 self-regression caught + fixed: per-cohort OG share-cards were serving `cache-control: public, max-age=0` (no CDN cache) on prod despite my T99 setting `max-age=0, s-maxage=86400, stale-while-revalidate=86400`. Vercel was stripping s-maxage. Verified via curl T105: `https://www.greenlifecannabis.com/heroes/veterans/opengraph-image` → `cache-control: public, max-age=0` + `x-vercel-cache: MISS` (every share-crawler hit re-rendered Satori). Adopted proven blog OG pattern (live + working since v8.205): `public, max-age=86400, s-maxage=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800` — same value for browser + CDN. Sister of scc v13.7605. Methodology: T99 was verified live for response-200, but cache-headers verification was skipped — added to standard post-deploy verification recipe. tsc clean.
// 20.005 — 🛡️ Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only header added — kicks off Doug-action #2 from round-3 close. Pre-fix glw + scc were the lone CSP outliers across the 6-site stack. Permissive starting policy: default-src 'self', script-src + style-src 'unsafe-inline' (iHJ Boost requires), img-src https: (vendor logos), connect-src + frame-src allow iHJ Boost subdomains + Vercel Analytics + GA4 + Cloudflare/recaptcha trust-token endpoints. **Report-Only CANNOT block requests** — browsers log violations to DevTools Console only. Observation window ~1-2 weeks. Doug observes via Chrome DevTools on key pages before flipping to enforce mode. Sister scc v13.7705. tsc clean.
// 20.105 — 🛡️ NEW `/api/csp-report` edge route + `report-uri` directive added to CSP-Report-Only header — completes T108 observation infrastructure. Pre-T109 violations only logged to per-user Chrome DevTools Console (Doug couldn't aggregate). Now: browsers POST W3C-spec CSP-violation JSON to `/api/csp-report` (edge runtime, force-dynamic), endpoint format-only-logs to console.error which Vercel Runtime Logs auto-capture cross-visitor. Doug can `vercel logs` or open Vercel Dashboard → Logs filter to grep `[csp-violation]` during the 1-2 week observation window. Anti-spam: 4KB body cap, malformed reports drop silently with 204. No PII concerns (only URL/directive strings, no body content). Sticking with report-uri (deprecated but wider support — Safari+Firefox only honor report-uri; Chromium honors both); future tick can add report-to + Reporting-Endpoints for richer Chromium reports. Sister scc v13.7805. tsc clean.
// 20.205 — 🚀 Homepage CDN-cache fix — removed `cookies()` call that was opting `/` out of CDN caching despite `revalidate=60` (TTFB ~210ms / 4× cannagent). Per Doug-greenlit Option (A) from OWNER_ACTION_QUEUE perf item: server now fetches all deals (`includeAppOnly: true`) and renders to HTML; new client-only `<AppOnlyDealsFilter />` reads `glw_pwa_installed` cookie post-hydrate and `display:none`s app-only cards via `data-app-only="1"` attr. Tradeoff: ~50ms pre-hydrate flicker for non-installed customers seeing app-only cards. PWA-install carrot preserved. Sister scc port queued separately — same `app/page.tsx` pattern, same fix shape.
// 20.305 — 🛡️ NEW arc-guard `scripts/check-csp-report-only.mjs` — pins T108 v20.005 (CSP-RO header) + T109 v20.105 (report-uri + endpoint) against regression. 4 checks: CSP_REPORT_ONLY const declared, Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only header registered, report-uri /api/csp-report directive present, app/api/csp-report/route.ts endpoint file exists. Catch-rate verified via injection. Same heuristic-presence pattern as `check-medical-clinic-ld-completeness.mjs` + `check-breadcrumb-ld-id.mjs` on GW. Sister scc same-port. tsc clean.
// 20.405 — 🚀 Homepage CDN-cache fix part 2 — v20.205 was incomplete. Verified post-deploy that `cache-control: private, no-cache, no-store` was STILL being set on `/` despite removing `cookies()`. Root cause: `fetchClosureStatus()` defaults to `cache: "no-store"` when no `revalidate` opt is passed (per `lib/closure-status.ts:63`). Server Components calling `fetch({ cache: "no-store" })` opt the entire page out of ISR. Fix: pass `{ revalidate: 60 }` matching the page's revalidate window. Now upstream closure-status fetch participates in 60s ISR cycle instead of forcing the page dynamic. Sister scc port queued.
// 20.505 — 🚀 /menu CDN-cache fix — same pattern as homepage v20.205+v20.405 ported to GLW's most-visited customer page. Removed `cookies()` reading `glw_pwa_installed` + the dependent `getActiveDeals({ includeAppOnly: isInstalled })` filter. Now fetches all deals server-side; passes `appOnly` flag through MenuFallback's `featuredDeal` prop + adds `data-app-only` to MenuActiveDealsStrip cards + MenuFallback deal pill. Mounts `<AppOnlyDealsFilter />` so PWA-only cards display:none for non-installed visitors post-hydrate. Plus passes `{revalidate:60}` to fetchClosureStatus matching homepage fix. ISR now engages on /menu — most-trafficked customer page on the site. Verify post-deploy via curl `cache-control: public` + `x-nextjs-prerender: 1`. Sister scc port queued.
