// 20.705 — 🛡️ NEW pre-push gates infrastructure on glw — wires all 9 arc-guards (site-url-defense + og-completeness + duplicate-brand-title + og-image-shape + per-route-og-image + title-length-html + description-length-html + button-type + csp-report-only) into `.githooks/pre-push` with TypeScript check upstream. Pre-T118 these gates existed as scripts but were only run via direct `node scripts/check-X.mjs` invocations — pushes could land violations of any of them without blocking. Now: every `git push` runs `tsc --noEmit` + 9 build-gates; failures with detailed remediation message + bypass instructions. Activated via NEW `scripts/setup-hooks.sh` (sets `git config core.hooksPath .githooks` — idempotent, run once per developer machine). Verified clean 9/9 via dry-run `bash .githooks/pre-push`. Sister of GW v2.97.S0 17/17 pre-push extension (T117). Sister scc v13.8405. Round-5 3rd ship completes the cross-stack arc-guard enforcement parity. Doug-action note: developers on existing checkouts must run `bash scripts/setup-hooks.sh` once to activate. tsc clean.
