// 35.105 — 📰 Blog Article JSON-LD rigor — SEO audit 2026-05-14 Tier-1 #4 fix. Two field upgrades on `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`'s `articleSchema`: (a) `dateModified` is now ALWAYS emitted (defaults to `datePublished` when post SSoT lacks an explicit `updatedAt`) — Google uses this as a freshness ranking signal in news/blog SERP categories. Pre-fix only emitted when `updatedAt` was set, so 5 of 6 static posts had no `dateModified` field at all. Not a fabrication: same-day publication is a real signal, not a backdated edit. (b) `author` flipped from `{ "@type": "Organization", name: STORE.name }` to `{ "@type": "Person", name, url }` — Google's "About this result" panel + Anthropic/Perplexity AI source-citation weighting both prefer Person-bound authors over Org. Per-post override comes from new optional `post.author?: { name, url }` field on `Post` type (`lib/posts.ts`); when absent, defaults to store owner Doug Cundiff at `${STORE.website}/about#owner` — this is a known-true author of record (Doug + staff write every post) pending per-post authorship metadata. (c) `mainEntityOfPage` added (`{ "@type": "WebPage", "@id": url }`) — pairs with `@id`/`url` to fully resolve Article ↔ WebPage entity for AI scrapers. (d) `publisher` Organization reference retained separately as Article schema requires both. `apiPostToPost` extended to pass through `updatedAt` + `authorName` + `authorUrl` from the inv CMS so future CMS posts pick this up automatically. Sister scc v26.405 same-push. typecheck queued.
// 35.405 — ⚡ Perf audit (PERF_AUDIT_NEAR_PAGES_2026_05_14.md) — `next.config.ts` `images:` block now declares `formats: ["image/avif", "image/webp"]` + `minimumCacheTTL: 60 * 60 * 24 * 30` (30 days). Pre-fix: only `remotePatterns` was set, so Next/Image defaulted to WebP-only output + 4hr edge cache. AVIF compresses ~20% smaller than WebP; combined with the longer TTL this cuts byte-weight + cold-edge re-optimization cost across every `<Image>`-rendered surface (menu, brand-logo cards, hero, blog covers, /near hero bands). AVIF support: Chrome/Edge/Firefox/Safari 16+ — older Safari + IE fall through to WebP fallback automatically via `Accept` header negotiation; final fallback is the original format. Next/Image fingerprints `_next/image` URLs so cache-bust on source change is automatic regardless of TTL — 30 days is safe even for menu thumbnails that update on every CMS edit. Sister scc v26.705 same-push. typecheck queued.
// 35.805 — 🎖️ Heroes cohort pages — long-form descriptive body + canonical FAQ expansion. Pre-fix: 5 cohort pages (/heroes/veterans · /military · /first-responders · /healthcare · /teachers) had strong hero + recognition copy + 3-4 cohort-specific FAQs + FAQPage + Offer + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD + visible Breadcrumb, but ZERO long-form descriptive body between hero and "What to bring" — high-intent long-tail SEO surface ("veterans discount cannabis Wenatchee" / "healthcare worker discount Wenatchee dispensary" / etc.) was thin on word-count, leaving Google nothing to extract beyond hero one-liner + ID-examples list. **Fix:** NEW `longForm: string[]` field on the cohort `Cohort` type — 4 paragraphs per cohort (~350-500 words), rendered as a new top-of-body section between hero band + "What to bring" block. Paragraph structure (cityCopy pattern): (1) who qualifies + which credential we accept + 21+ ID reminder; (2) how the discount works — 30% off in-store subtotal, no stacking, every category, online vs in-store, loyalty-points carry-over; (3) Wenatchee-specific cohort context (Confluence VFW Post 3617 + American Legion Post 10 for vets / Yakima Training Center commute for active military / Chelan County Sheriff + Wenatchee Valley Fire + Lifeline Ambulance for first responders / Confluence Health + Cascade Medical + Three Rivers for healthcare / Wenatchee SD + Eastmont + Cashmere + WV Tech for teachers) — best-staff + Since 2014 tenure framing per memory pin `project_wenatchee_positioning_best_staff`; (4) how to use it at the counter — first-visit verification, automatic forward, no re-credentialing. **Voice:** WAC 314-55-155 STRICT — every sentence describes the program or the shop, zero effect/medical/product claims. Unicode U+2019 apostrophes throughout, no exclamation marks, never "veteran-owned" or "locally-owned" framing for Wenatchee (Doug 2026-05-02 ownership-change directive — eligibility-for-vets framing IS fine, ownership-claim is not). /menu CTA preserved