// 36.085 — 🐛 `lib/posts.ts:613` `isPublished()` UTC-drift fix — closes v32.805 incomplete-port. v32.805 changelog "Sites lifted" enumerated 3 sites (/llms.txt + /llms-full.txt + lib/posts.ts:554 publishedAt fallback) but missed `isPublished(p, asOf = new Date())` at posts.ts:613. **Bug:** `const today = asOf.toISOString().slice(0, 10)` returns UTC date — for the 7-8h evening Pacific window (5pm PT until midnight UTC), `today` already reads as "tomorrow" so future-dated blog posts become visible 7-8h early. Customer-facing impact: a post authored `publishedAt: "2026-05-15"` becomes visible at 5pm PT on 2026-05-14, when the operator expected it visible 2026-05-15 00:00 PT. **Fix:** one-line swap to `const today = storeToday(asOf)` — `storeToday` already imported on line 2 from previous v32.805 partial port. **Detection:** caught during v36.065 pacific-date-coverage sister-port audit (the narrow inv-shape arc-guard does NOT match `<param>.toISOString().slice(0, 10)` form, so this slipped past the new defense too — flagged as side-finding then closed in this ship). **Math:** `storeToday(asOf)` uses `Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-CA", { timeZone: STORE_TZ })` to produce a Pacific YYYY-MM-DD string regardless of server TZ. Sister scc v27.385 same-push (identical incomplete-port at posts.ts:1085). tsc clean.
